3C%2Fa%3E%20surprised%20election%20officials.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20may%20try%20to%20find%20a%20safe%20harbor%20in%20the%20culture%20war%20du%20jour%2C%20but%20Americans%20are%20far%20more%20agitated%20about%20abortion%20restrictions%20than%20worried%20about%20their%20gas%20grills.%20Just%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20abortion%20was%20still%20a%20taboo%20issue%20in%20Democratic%20politics.%20Their%20leaders%20defended%20the%20Hyde%20Amendment%20that%20banned%20most%20federal%20funds%20from%20being%20used%20for%20an%20abortion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20strategists%20are%20plotting%20votes%20%3Cem%3Eguaranteeing%3C%2Fem%3E%20abortion%20rights%20in%20just%20about%20every%20state%20they%20can%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbortion%20rights%20activists%20have%20now%20stood%20down%20efforts%20to%20pass%20restrictions%20in%20Kansas%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20and%20Montana.%20Meanwhile%2C%20they've%20written%20abortion%20protections%20into%20the%20constitution%20in%20states%20such%20as%20Michigan.%20Ohio%20may%20very%20well%20join%20its%20neighbor%20later%20this%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConservatives%20were%20elated%20that%20they%20realized%20their%20decades-long%20effort%20to%20gut%20Roe.%20Instead%2C%20it%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20reoccurring%20nightmare%20whenever%20the%20issue%20is%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnti-abortion%20groups%20that%20were%20once%20in%20almost%20lockstep%20with%20GOP%20leaders%20are%20warring%20with%20presidential%20candidates%20and%20lawmakers%20who%20refuse%20to%20back%20nationwide%20abortion%20bans%20that%20range%20from%20unpopular%20(15%20weeks)%20to%20a%20near-career%20ender%20(6%20weeks).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20say%20abortion%20opponents%20have%20struck%20out.%20Roe's%20reversal%20opened%20the%20door%20to%20abortion%20bans%20that%20were%20ready%20to%20go.%20Abortion%20rights%20activists%20have%20been%20left%20to%20fight%20a%20bevy%20of%20court%20battles%20with%20limited%20successes%20in%20often%20heavily%20conservative%20courts.%20More%20states%20are%20trying%20to%20enact%20greater%20bans%2C%20such%20as%20Florida%2C%20where%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%20pushed%20a%20ban%20on%20almost%20all%20abortions%20after%206%20weeks%20into%20law.%20Some%20Republicans%20want%20to%20go%20even%20further%2C%20by%20restricting%20pills%20used%20for%20medicated%20abortions%20or%20by%20limiting%20out-of-state%20travel%20for%20abortions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabortion-pills-polling-gop-republican-doomed-election-chances-generation-2023-4%5C%22%3EPolls%20show%3C%2Fa%3E%20those%20types%20of%20restrictions%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F01%2Fus%2Felections%2Ftimes-siena-poll-registered-voters-crosstabs.html%5C%22%3Ealmost%20comically%20unpopular%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20result%20may%20quickly%20be%20the%20least%20of%20the%20GOP's%20worries.%20The%20prospect%20of%20the%20issue%20coming%20up%20in%20a%20key%202024%20state%20is%20becoming%20more%20likely%20each%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActivists%20in%20Arizona%20have%20already%20taken%20steps%20to%20put%20the%20issue%20on%20the%20ballot%20next%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fohio-gop-issue-1-abortion-analysis-results-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691541146000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d1289b20f1cf0019cc3428%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fohio-gop-issue-1-abortion-analysis-results-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Republicans%20tried%20to%20kneecap%20an%20abortion%20rights%20amendment%20months%20before%20it%20came%20before%20voters.%20In%20return%2C%20they%20received%20a%20major%20rebuke.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%