I's%20scraping%20bots.%20You%20can%20too.%20(I%20don't%20know%20if%20this%20is%20the%20secret%20one%20we%20couldn't%20block%20before%20or%20if%20that%20one%20is%20still%20in%20use.)%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fclarkesworld%2Fstatus%2F1688600561447268370%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20Neil%20Clarke%2C%20editor%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclarkesworldmagazine.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClarkesworld%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20science%20fiction%20and%20fantasy%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETrust%20is%20evaporating%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Clarke%20about%20his%20decision%2C%20and%20his%20responses%20reveal%20how%20quickly%20trust%20has%20evaporated%20between%20online%20content%20creators%20and%20AI%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20and%20other%20'AI'%20creators%20have%20demonstrated%20repeatedly%20that%20they%20have%20no%20respect%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20authors%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20other%20creative%20professionals.%20Their%20products%20are%20largely%20based%20on%20the%20copyrighted%20works%20of%20others%2C%20taken%20without%20authorization%20or%20compensation%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20wrote%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BThey%20repeatedly%20defend%20the%20use%20of%20these%20practices%20and%20have%20only%20recently%20identified%20this%20bot.%20It's%20not%20entirely%20clear%20that%20opting%20out%20of%20this%20bot%20(and%20CCBot)%20will%20be%20sufficient%20to%20avoid%20having%20content%20harvested%20by%20OpenAI.%20Their%20track%20record%20on%20transparency%20leaves%20much%20to%20be%20desired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECCBot%20is%20another%20digital%20spider%20that%20crawls%20the%20web%20collecting%20all%20the%20content.%20This%20is%20run%20by%20an%20organization%20called%20Common%20Crawl%2C%20which%20is%20a%20major%20supplier%20of%20training%20data%20for%20AI%20models.%20Common%20Crawl%20stores%20all%20this%20information%20regularly%2C%20so%20even%20if%20you%20block%20its%20bot%20now%2C%20your%20data%20has%20already%20probably%20been%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20unaware%20of%20anyone%20that%20has%20managed%20to%20get%20Common%20Crawl%20to%20remove%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20tried%2C%20but%20have%20had%20no%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Opt-in'%20not%20'opt-out'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClarke%20and%20others%20are%20now%20calling%20for%20these%20AI%20spiderbots%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bopt-in%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bopt-out.%26quot%3B%20Right%20now%2C%20OpenAI%20scrapes%20everyone's%20data%20as%20the%20default%2C%20and%20creators%20must%20take%20steps%20to%20opt%20out%20and%20actively%20block%20it.%20An%20%26quot%3Bopt-in%26quot%3B%20approach%20would%20require%20OpenAI%20to%20ask%20permission%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20collection%20methods%20for%20these%20models%20must%20become%20strictly%20opt-in.%20Many%20people%20will%20not%20find%20out%20how%20to%20protect%20their%20work%20until%20it%20has%20already%20been%20taken%2C%20yet%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSince%20we%20are%20presently%20unable%20to%20have%20our%20content%20removed%20from%20existing%20models%20and%20scraped%20data%20sets%2C%20opt-out%20is%20not%20enough.%20It%20is%20not%20our%20responsibility%20to%20provide%20data%20for%20these%20companies%2C%20nor%20should%20they%20be%20allowed%20to%20simply%20take%20it%20without%20consent%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20benefits%20they%20imagine%20coming%20from%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20OpenAI%20about%20all%20this%20on%20Tuesday%20morning.%20The%20company%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPaying%20for%20AI%20training%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20made%20an%20effort%20to%20respect%20some%20online%20data.%20GPTbot%20is%20now%20designed%20to%20filter%20out%20sources%20that%20require%20paywall%20access%20and%20to%20remove%20other%20sources%20known%20to%20gather%20personally%20identifiable%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20recently%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fopenai-chatgpt-associated-press-ap-f86f84c5bcc2f3b98074b38521f5f75a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edeal%20with%20the%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20OpenAI%20will%20pay%20to%20license%20AP%20content%20for%20AI%20training%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20company%20paid%20for%20this%20data%2C%20why%20doesn't%20it%20also%20pay%20for%20everyone%20else's%20information%2C%20too%3F%20I%20asked%20the%20company%20and%20it%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Block%20it'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20hasn't%20contacted%20Neil%20Clarke%20at%20Clarkesworld%20about%20paying%20for%20his%20online%20content.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20been%20approached%20to%20license%20works%20we%20published%2C%20nor%20would%20we%20be%20open%20to%20it.%20I'm%20unable%20to%20think%20of%C2%A0anything%20they%20could%20say%20or%20do%20that%20would%20change%20my%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20is%20Clarke's%20advice%20for%20other%20online%20content%20creators%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20GPTbot%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20short%20I'd%20say%20'block%20it'%20and%20suggest%20they%20reach%20out%20to%20lawmakers%20to%20express%20their%20concern%20regarding%20past%2C%20present%2C%20and%20future%20data%20collection%20methodologies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20blocking%20GPTbot%3F%20Are%20you%20blocking%20Googlebot%20or%20CCbot%2C%20too%3F%20We'd%20like%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Reach%20out%20at%20abarr%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Googlebot%20crawls%20a%20website%20and%20scrapes%20content%2C%20that%20process%20ends%20up%20sending%20us