m%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102546600%2Cimgsize-24732.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpolls-unlikely-this-year-pak-ministers%2Farticleshow%2F102546583.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102546583.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20home%20and%20defence%20ministers%20spoke%20on%20Tuesday%20%E2%80%94%20a%20day%20before%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20%E2%80%94%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20delay%20in%20holding%20the%20next%20general%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpolls-unlikely-this-year-pak-ministers%2Farticleshow%2F102546583.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpolls-unlikely-this-year-pak-ministers%2Famp_articleshow%2F102546583.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpolls-unlikely-this-year-pak-ministers%2Famp_articleshow%2F102546583.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20Outcry%20Over%20Bilkis%20Bano's%20Rapists%20Walking%20Free%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20Says...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPublic%20outcry%20will%20not%20affect%20judicial%20decisions%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asserted%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20as%20it%20began%20weighing%20the%20legality%20of%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20all%20the%2011%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gang-rape%20case%20and%20murder%20of%20seven%20of%20her%20family%20members%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20agitations%20and%20society's%20outcry%20will%20not%20have%20an%20effect%20on%20its%20decisions%20and%20that%20it%20will%20go%20only%20by%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPublic%20outcry%20will%20not%20affect%20our%20judicial%20decisions.%20We%20will%20consider%20only%20legal%20submissions%20and%20will%20not%20go%20by%20this%20(public%20anger%20over%20the%20incident).%20Suppose%2C%C2%A0there%20is%20no%20public%20outcry.%20Are%20we%20supposed%20to%20uphold%20the%20order%3F%20If%20there%20is%20a%20public%20outcry%2C%20does%20it%20mean%20it%20is%20a%20wrong%20order%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20told%20advocate%20Shobha%20Gupta%2C%20appearing%20for%20Bilkis%20Bano.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20observation%20came%20after%20Ms%20Gupta%20submitted%20that%20%26quot%3Bpublic%20outcry%26quot%3B%20is%20one%20of%20the%20important%20factors%20to%20be%20considered%20while%20granting%20remission%20to%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20there%20was%20an%20outcry%20in%20society%20after%20the%20convicts%20in%20the%20case%20were%20released%20and%20there%C2%A0were%20agitations%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20hearing%20began%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano's%20counsel%20told%20the%20top%20court%20the%20Additional%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%2C%20Prisons%20and%20Correctional%20Administration%2C%20Gujarat%20had%20tendered%20a%20negative%20opinion%20about%20remission%20to%20the%20convicts%20and%20not%20recommended%20premature%20release%20of%20one%20of%20them%20-%20Radheshyam%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20after%20Radheshyam%20Shah's%20plea%20seeking%20premature%20release%20under%20the%20Gujarat%20government's%20July%209%2C%201992%20policy%20on%20remission%20was%20declined%20by%20the%20Gujarat%20High%20Court%2C%20he%20approached%20the%20top%20court%20in%20a%20writ%20petition%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20is%20this%20writ%20petition%20before%20this%20court%20maintainable%20after%20he%20has%20already%20availed%20remedy%20under%20Article%20226%20(before%20HC)%2C%20accepted%20order%20and%20acted%20on%20it%3F%20For%20what%20purpose%20did%20he%20come%20to%20this%20court%2C%20and%20how%20did%20this%20court%20entertain%20the%20petition%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20bench%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20226%20gives%20high%20courts%20the%20power%20to%20issue%20instructions%2C%20orders%2C%20and%20writs%20to%20any%20person%20or%20authority%2C%20including%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadheysham%20Shah%20had%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20remission%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20he%20had%20completed%2015%20years%20and%204%20months%20in%20jail.%20He%20was%20sent%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20by%20a%20CBI%20court%20in%20Mumbai%20in%202008.%20In%20accordance%20with%20the%20rules%20then%20in%20force%2C%20a%20convict%20could%20apply%20for%20remission%20after%2014%20years%2C%20which%20was%20then%20considered%20the%20period%20of%20life%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHearing%20Shah's%20petition%2C%20the%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20to%20look%20into%20the%20matter%20and%20decide%20within%20two%20months%20whether%20he%20could%20be%20granted%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano's%20counsel%20Gupta%20submitted%20that%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20directing%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20to%20consider%20his%20plea%2C%20everything%20got%20expedited%20and%20all%20the%20convicts%20got%20released%20on%20August%2015%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Indira%20Jaising%2C%20appearing%20in%20one%20of%20the%20PILs%2C%20recalled%20how%20the%20convicts%20were%20garlanded%20and%20felicitated%20and%20statements%20were%20made%20about%20their%20being%20Brahmins%20who%20cannot%20commit%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditional%20Solicitor%20General%20SV%20Raju%20said%20those%20who%20garlanded%20the%20released%20convicts%20were%20their%20family%20members.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20wrong%20in%20garlanding%20by%20a%20family%20member%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20fag%20end%20of%20the%20hearing%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20top%20court%20said%20it%20will%20hear%20arguments%20on%20August%209%20on%20the%20locus%20standi%20of%20multiple%20people%20who%20have%20filed%20PILs%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gang-rape%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20petition%20filed%20by%20Bilkis%20Bano%2C%20several%20other%20PILs%20including%20one%20by%20CPI(M)%20leader%20Subhashini%20Ali%2C%20independent%20journalist%20Revati%20Laul%20and%20former%20vice-chancellor%20of%20Lucknow%20University%20Roop%20Rekha%20Verma%20have%20challenged%20the%20remission.%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20has%20also%20filed%20a%20PIL%20against%20the%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Sidharth%20Luthra%2C%20appearing%20for%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%2C%20told%20the%20bench%20that%20once%20the%20victim%20individual%20is%20in%20court%2C%20others%20may%20not%20have%20a%20locus%20standi%20(entitlement%20to%20bring%20a%20lawsuit%20in%20court)%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20this%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gang-rape%20case%20and%20murder%20of%20seven%20of%20her%20family%20members%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20chased%20her%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bblood%20thirsty%20approach%26quot%3B%20to%20hunt%20Muslims%20and%20kill%20them%2C%20the%20top%20court%20was%20told%20on%20Monday%2C%20as%20it%20commenced%20the%20final%20hearing%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20challenging%20the%20remission%20granted%20last%20year%20to%20all%20the%2011%20convicts%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20on%20April%2018%20questioned%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20over%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20the%2011%20convicts%2C%20saying%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20offence%20should%20have%20been%20considered%20before%20showing%20leniency%2C%20and%20wondered%20if%20there%20was%20any%20application%20of%20mind.%20All%20of%20them%20had%20walked%20free%20on%20August%2015%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsking%20for%20reasons%20for%20the%20premature%20release%20of%20the%20convicts%2C%20the%20top%20court%20had%20also%20questioned%20frequent%20parole%20granted%20to%20them%20during%20their%20incarceration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20(remission)%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20grace%2C%20which%20should%20be%20proportional%20to%20the%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerming%20Bilkis%20Bano's%20gang-rape%20and%20the%20murder%20of%20her%20family%20members%20a%20%26quot%3Bhorrendous%26quot%3B%20act%2C%20the%20top%20court%20had%20on%20March%2027%20asked%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20whether%20uniform%20standards%2C%20as%20followed%20in%20other%20murder%20cases%2C%20were%20applied%20while%20granting%20remission%20to%20the%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano%20was%2021%20and%20five%20months%20pregnant%20when%20she%20was%20gang-raped%20while%20fleeing%20the%20communal%20riots%20that%20broke%20out%20after%20the%20Godhra%20train-burning%20incident.%20Her%20three-year-old%20daughter%20was%20among%20the%20seven%20family%20members%20killed%20in%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2011%20convicts%20granted%20premature%20release%20are%20Jaswantbhai%20Nai%2C%20Govindbhai%20Nai%2C%20Shailesh%20Bhatt%2C%20Radheshyam%20Shah%2C%20Bipin%20Chandra%20Joshi%2C%20Kesarbhai%20Vohania%2C%20Pradeep%20Mordhiya%2C%20Bakabhai%20Vohania%2C%20Rajubhai%20Soni%2C%20Mitesh%20Bhatt%2C%20and%20Ramesh%20Chandana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691518740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-08%2Fp179al0g_bilkis-bano-ani-650_625x300_17_August_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpublic-outcry-wont-affect-decisions-supreme-court-on-bilkis-bano-case-4280677%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Public%20outcry%20will%20not