ing-off-period-for-retired-stars-t20-world-cup-winner-reacts-4280934%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Funfair-on-reports-of-bccis-cooling-off-period-for-retired-stars-t20-world-cup-winner-reacts-4280934%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Funfair-on-reports-of-bccis-cooling-off-period-for-retired-stars-t20-world-cup-winner-reacts-4280934%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%20Hearing%3A%20CJI%20Says%20Brexit-Type%20Referendum%20Not%20Possible%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192226%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000175B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EChief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20has%20said%20a%20Brexit-type%20referendum%20cannot%20be%20envisaged%20in%20India%2C%20responding%20to%20petitioners%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fday-2-of-article-370-case-constituent-assembly-is-distinguishable-from-partisan-parliament-sc-told%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20said%20it%20was%20read%20down%20through%20a%20series%20of%20%E2%80%9Cexecutive%20acts%E2%80%9D%20without%20considering%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHearing%20the%20case%20for%20the%20third%20day%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20August%208%2C%20the%20CJI%20said%20that%20in%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%20such%20as%20India%2C%20public%20opinion%20is%20sought%20through%20established%20institutions%20such%20as%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20recourse%20to%20public%20opinion%20has%20to%20be%20sought%20through%20established%20institutions.%20You%20cannot%20envisage%20a%20Brexit-type%20referendum%E2%80%A6%20That%20was%20a%20political%20decision%20taken%20by%20the%20then%20government%20in%20the%20U.K%E2%80%A6%20But%20within%20a%20constitution%20like%20ours%2C%20there%20is%20no%20question%20of%20a%20referendum%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Farticle-370-hearing-india-seeks-public-opinion-through-established-institutions-not-brexit-type-referendums-says-cji%2Farticle67172076.ece%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20had%20accused%20the%20Union%20government%20of%20reading%20down%20the%20Article%20%E2%80%9Cunilaterally%E2%80%9D%20without%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20understand%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20want%20to%20sever%20such%20a%20special%20relationship%20with%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20you%20had%20to%20ultimately%20seek%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20people.%20The%20will%20of%20the%20people%20was%20central%20to%20this%20decision.%20It%20should%20have%20been%20a%20political%20decision%E2%80%A6%20What%20happened%20in%20Brexit%3F%20There%20was%20no%20constitutional%20provision%20for%20a%20referendum.%20Yet%2C%20they%20asked%20for%20public%20opinion%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20had%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20Article%20was%20abrogated%20through%20a%20series%20of%20%E2%80%9Cexecutive%20acts%E2%80%9D%2C%20beginning%20with%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Legislative%20Assembly%20and%20the%20state%20government.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20and%20a%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370%20(3)%20was%20tweaked%20to%20%E2%80%9Csidestep%20the%20pre-condition%20of%20getting%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20now%20defunct%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Constituent%20Assembly%20before%20declaring%20Article%20370%20inoperative%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%20Sibal%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3