e%20Congress%20directed%20three%20pointed%20questions%20at%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20today%20and%20sought%20to%20know%20why%20he%20had%20not%20visited%20Manipur%20in%20the%20over%20three%20months%20since%20the%20state%20began%20witnessing%20ethnic%20violence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpening%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20the%20government%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Congress%20MP%20Gaurav%20Gogoi%20tore%20into%20the%20Centre%20and%20said%20he%20had%20three%20questions%20to%20ask%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20not%20visit%20Manipur%3F%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20went%2C%20MPs%20from%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20went%20and%20even%20the%20Home%20Minister%20and%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Home%20(Nityanand%20Rai)%20visited%20the%20state.%20Being%20the%20chief%20of%20the%20country%2C%20why%20did%20PM%20Modi%20not%20go%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gogoi%20asked%20amid%20the%20thumping%20of%20desks%20by%20opposition%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20question%20from%20the%20MP%2C%20who%20is%20the%20deputy%20leader%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20was%20why%20it%20took%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20nearly%2080%20days%20to%20say%20anything%20on%20the%20Manipur%20violence%20issue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20he%20did%20speak%2C%20he%20did%20so%20for%20only%2030%20seconds.%20Since%20then%2C%20there%20have%20been%20no%20words%20of%20sympathy%20and%20no%20appeal%20for%20peace%20from%20him.%20His%20ministers%20say%20we%20will%20speak.%20Nobody%20has%20stopped%20them%2C%20but%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20words%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20a%20minister's.%20If%20PM%20Modi%20takes%20a%20step%20to%20ensure%20peace%2C%20it%20will%20carry%20more%20weight%20than%20that%20of%20a%20minister%20or%20an%20MP%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Gogoi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20question%20was%20on%20Manipur%20Chief%20Minister%20N%20Biren%20Singh.%20Mr%20Gogoi%20asked%20why%20PM%20Modi%20had%20not%20sacked%20the%20chief%20minister%20so%20far.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20polls%20were%20approaching%20and%20you%20needed%20to%20do%20your%20politics%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20you%20changed%20the%20chief%20minister%20there%2C%20not%20once%2C%20but%20twice.%20Ahead%20of%20elections%20in%20Uttarakhand%2C%20you%20changed%20the%20state%20chief%20minister%20probably%20four%20times.%20A%20change%20was%20made%20in%20Tripura%20too.%20Why%20have%20you%20reserved%20special%20blessings%20for%20the%20Manipur%20chief%20minister%2C%20who%20has%20himself%20accepted%20that%20there%20was%20an%20intelligence%20failure%20because%20of%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Congress%20MP%20from%20Assam%20asked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListing%20out%20his%20reasons%20for%20PM%20Modi's%20silence%2C%20Mr%20Gogoi%20alleged%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20because%20the%20state%20government%20failed%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20and%20the%20Home%20Department%20and%20the%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20failed%20to%20handle%20the%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20third%20reason%20for%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20silence%20is%20that%20he%20does%20not%20like%20to%20accept%20his%20mistakes.%20He%20will%20never%20accept%20publicly%20that%20his%20state%20government%20has%20failed.%20He%20prefers%20remaining%20silent%20to%20accepting%20his%20mistakes%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gogoi%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20MP%20said%20the%20opposition%20had%20moved%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%20not%20for%20numbers%2C%20but%20to%20get%20justice%20for%20Manipur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Manipur%20is%20burning%2C%20entire%20India%20is%20burning%2C%20if%20Manipur%20is%20divided%2C%20the%20country%20is%20divided.%20It%20was%20our%20demand%20that%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20country%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20should%20come%20to%20the%20House%20and%20speak%20about%20Manipur.%20However%2C%20he%20kept%20a%20'maun%20vrat'%20(vow%20of%20silence)%20that%20he%20will%20neither%20speak%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20nor%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20Through%20the%20no-confidence%20motion%2C%20we%20want%20to%20break%20his%20vow%20of%20silence%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20PTI%20report%20quoted%20the%20Congress%20MP%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20were%20gasping%20for%20breath%20during%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20Covid%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20was%20seeking%20votes%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20When%20women%20were%20being%20assaulted%20in%20Manipur%2C%20the%20PM%20was%20seeking%20votes%20in%20Karnataka.%20What%20kind%20of%20nationalism%20is%20this%20that%20places%20power%20above%20the%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gogoi%20asked%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MP%20said%20it%20was%20a%20matter%20of%20grave%20concern%20that%20a%20government%20which%20talked%20about%20%26quot%3Bone%20India%26quot%3B%20had%20created%20%26quot%3Btwo%20Manipurs%20-%20one%20living%20in%20the%20hills%20and%20the%20other%20in%20the%20valley%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20that%20former%20prime%20minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20had%20visited%20Gujarat%20after%20the%20riots%20in%202002.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHitting%20out%20at%20PM%20Modi%20on%20his%20silence%20on%20important%20issues%2C%20Mr%20Gogoi%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20award-winning%20women%20wrestlers%20were%20protesting%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20remained%20silent.%20When%20750%20farmers%20lost%20their%20lives%20during%20the%20agitation%2C%20the%20PM%20was%20silent.%20In%202020%2C%20when%20Delhi%20witnessed%20riots%20and%20a%20foreign%20leader%20was%20visiting%20India%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20remained%20silent.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20questioned%20the%20government%20on%20incursions%20by%20China%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20remained%20silent.%20When%20a%20former%20lieutenant%20governor%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20said%20he%20had%20sought%20protection%20for%20the%20soldiers%20in%20Pulwama%20but%20was%20turned%20down%2C%20the%20PM%20remained%20silent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20MP%20alleged.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691505480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F671j18mg_gaurav-gogoi-650_625x300_08_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-visit-manipur-congress-3-big-questions-to-pm-modi-4280586%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Congress%20directed%20three%20pointed%20questions%20at%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20today%20and%20sought%20to%20know%20why%20he%20had%20not%20visited%20Manipur%20in%20the%20over%20three%20months%20since%20the%20state%20began%20witnessing%20ethnic%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhy-didnt-you-visit-manipur-congress-3-big-questions-to-pm-modi-4280586%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Italian%20banks%20hit%20with%20surprise%20windfall%20tax%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691505323000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F5469%2Fproduction%2F_130690612_gettyimages-1509949466.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66440335%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20potential%20one-off%20tax%20on%20the%20profits%20banks%20earn%20from%20higher%20interest%20rates%20has%20seen%20shares%20plummet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A333%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66440335%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66440335.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-66440335.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Genders%20of%20Atrocity%3A%20Before%20Lynndie%20England%20There%20Was%20Ilse%20Koch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08144406%2F187141eb-5424-463f-be84-499b1480aeb0.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELynndie%20England%20captured%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20world%20when%2C%20in%202004%2C%20newspapers%20and%20media%20flashed%20photographs%20from%20one%20of%20earth%E2%80%99s%20darkest%20places%3A%20the%20Abu%20Ghraib%20prison%20in%20Baghdad.%20England%20was%20caught%20on%20camera%20threatening%20a%20naked%20Iraqi%20prisoner%20with%20a%20leashed%20dog%2C%20laughing%20at%20the%20humiliated%20prisoners%2C%20etc%2C%20and%20subsequent%20investigations%20and%20evidence%20revealed%20her%20active%20participation%20in%20the%20torture%20regime%20that%20was%20Abu%20Ghraib.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20her%20trial%20England%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20mistreatment%20of%20prisoners%2C%20and%20the%20media%20was%20divided%20on%20her%20role%3A%20victim%20or%20victimiser.%20Arguments%20that%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20behave%20in%20unspeakable%20fashion%20were%20countered%20with%20arguments%20that%20she%20knew%20exactly%20what%20she%20was%20doing.%20Was%20she%20scapegoated%20by%20both%20the%20military%20and%20the%20political%20bosses%20for%20being%20caught%20%E2%80%93%20the%20debate%20remains%20unresolvable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEngland%E2%80%99s%20story%20is%20not%2C%20however%2C%20a%20unique%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBefore%20England%2C%20and%20after%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20cases%20of%20women%20murderers%20that%20attract%20singular%20attention%20in%20the%20media%2C%20the%20allegedly%20%E2%80%98deviant%E2%80%99%20acts%20of%20women%20in%20situations%20such%20as%20war%2C%20genocide%20and%20torture%20have%20a%20long%20history%20in%20the%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%20which%2C%20naturally%2C%20begins%20at%20the%20gates%20of%20Auschwitz%2C%20Bergen-Belsen%20and%20Buchenwald.%20Later-day%20examples%20of%20girl-child%20soldiers%20now%20exist%20in%20documentation%20from%20Rwanda%2C%20the%20former%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbalkaninsight.com%2F2011%2F02%2F07%2Fbosnian-war-s-wicked-women-get-off-lightly%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EYugoslavia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20Darfur%20too.%20Evidence%20also%20shows%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20suicide%20bombers%20in%20conflict%20zones%20like%20Chechnya%20were%20women%2C%20thus%20situating%20them%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20heart%20of%20mass%20destruction.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDocumentary%20evidence%20tells%20us%20that%20at%20least%20a%20third%20of%20the%20female%20population%20in%20Germany%20were%20a%20part%20of%20Nazi%20Party%20organisation.%20A%20census%20from%201945%20lists%20a%20total%20of%2036%2C674%20male%20guards%20and%203%2C517%20female%20guards%20from%20the%20SS-Gefolge%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20nearly%2010%25%20of%20the%20guards%20were%20female.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EAt%20Auschwitz%2C%20between%201940%20and%201945%2C%20there%20were%20approximately%207%2C000%20male%20guards%20and%20200%20female%20guards.%20The%20secretarial%20staff%20in%20Berlin%2C%20nurses%20at%20the%20euthanasia%20camps%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fencyclopedia.ushmm.org%2Fcontent%2Fen%2Farticle%2Feuthanasia-program%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20notorious%20T4%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%2C%20teachers%20and%20workers%2C%20besides%20wives%20and%20girlfriends%20populated%20Nazi-occupied%20Europe%20and%20kept%20the%20Nazi%20machinery%20well-oiled%20during%20the%20excesses%20that%20occurred.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThey%20were%20not%20innocent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fthere-are-no-bystanders%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebystanders%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08141000%2F4c37000e-70af-4c8d-8736-f4232714248e.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08141000%2F4c37000e-70af-4c8d-8736-f4232714248e.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08141000%2F4c37000e-70af-4c8d-8736-f4232714248e-300x152.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667157%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAktion%20T4%20euthanasia%20camp.%20Photo%3A%20United%20States%20Holocaust%20Memorial%20Museum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWendy%20Lower%20cautions%20us%20against%20assumptions%20of%20German%20women%E2%80%99s%20absence%2C%20or%20victimhood%2C%20in%20the%20machinery%20in%20her%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fhgs%2Farticle-abstract%2F29%2F2%2F284%2F562414%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%26login%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHitler%E2%80%99s%20Furies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJust%20as%20the%20agency%20of%20women%20in%20history%20more%20generally%20is%20under%20appreciated%2C%20here%20too%20%E2%80%93%20and%20perhaps%20even%20more%20problematically%2C%20given%20the%20moral%20and%20legal%20implications%20%E2%80%93%20the%20agency%20of%20women%20in%20the%20crimes%C2%A0%20of%20the%20Third%20Reich%20has%20not%20been%20fully%20elaborated%20and%20explained.%20Vast%20numbers%20of%20ordinary%20German%20women%20were%20not%20victims%2C%20and%20routine%20forms%20of%20female%20participation%20in%20the%20Holocaust%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20disclosed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESusannah%20Heschel%20is%20categorical%20in%20her%20essay%2C%20%E2%80%98Does%20Atrocity%20have%20a%20Gender%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20there%20remains%20a%20tenacious%20belief%20to%20this%20day%20that%20women%20SS%20guards%20were%20not%20involved%20in%20murder%2C%20in%20fact%20they%20did%20participate%20in%20the%20selection%20of%20victims%20and%20in%20their%20murder%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20accompanying%20torture%20and%20brutality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENumerous%20memoirs%20attest%20to%20the%20brutality%20of%20women%20guards%2C%20including%20their%20arbitrary%20punishment%20and%20murder%20of%20inmates%2C%20and%20their%20selection%20of%20inmates%20for%20gassing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20scathing%20indictments%2C%20and%20history%E2%80%99s%20jury%20has%20its%20task%20cut%20out%20to%20determine%20the%20exact%20nature%20of%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20role%20as%20perpetrators%20of%2Fin%20Nazi%20atrocity.%20Whether%20the%20secretary%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehelped%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20compose%20memos%2C%20transmit%20orders%20and%20enable%20the%20planning%20of%20atrocities%20%E2%80%93%20thereby%20becoming%20desktop%20murderers%2C%20as%20Nazi%20bureaucrats%20were%20called%20%E2%80%93%20is%20open%20to%20question.%C2%A0%20Although%20their%20very%20position%20within%20the%20machinery%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20benefited%20from%20the%20system%2C%20suggests%20they%20are%2C%20in%20Michael%20Rothberg%E2%80%99s%20definition%20in%20the%20book%20of%20the%20same%20title%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EImplicated%20Subjects%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20contemporary%20times%2C%20women%20honouring%20indicted%20rapists%2C%20endorsing%20genocide%20or%20being%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20hate-speech%20and%20rabble-rousing%20if%20not%20direct%20political%20violence%20ought%20to%20take%20us%20back%20to%20the%20gendered%20nature%20of%20mass%20violence.%20Then%20there%20have%20been%20instances%20of%20women%20providing%20overt%20and%20covert%20support%20to%20raping%20and%20pillaging%20men.%20Finally%2C%20there%20are%20examples%20of%20women%20exhorting%20their%20men%20to%20inflict%20more%20humiliation%20and%20pain%20on%20other%20women.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20two%20strands%20to%20studies%20of%20the%20gender%20of%20atrocity.%20The%20first%20examines%20how%20such%20women%20as%20Grese%20or%20Koch%20are%20represented%20in%20history%2C%20both%20in%20their%20time%20and%20contemporary%2C%20so%20as%20to%20throw%20light%20on%20operations%20of%20gender%20in%20situations%20of%20mass%20violence%2C%20genocide%20and%20ethnic%20cleansing.%20The%20second%20studies%20the%20contexts%20in%20which%20a%20certain%20type%20of%20perpetrator%20emerges%20from%20among%20the%20women%20in%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBeauties%2C%20beasts%2C%20devils%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98When%20I%20laid%20eyes%20on%20Irma%20Griese%2C%20I%20felt%20sure%20that%20a%20woman%20of%20such%20beauty%20could%20not%20be%20cruel.%20For%20she%20was%20truly%20a%20blue-eyed%2C%20fair-haired%20%E2%80%9Cangel.%E2%80%9D%E2%80%99%20Thus%20writes%20Olga%20Lenyel%20in%20her%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20Chimneys%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Auschwitz.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20%E2%80%98angel%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98devil%E2%80%99%20slowly%20merge%20in%20such%20accounts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20nomenclatural%20excesses%20that%20mark%20the%20epithets%20of%20Nazi%20women%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20media%20and%20critical-historical%20construction%20of%20them.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIrme%20Grese%2C%20concentration%20camp%20guard%20at%20Auschwitz%20and%20later%20warden%20at%20Bergen-Belsen%2C%20was%20nicknamed%20%E2%80%98The%20Hyena%20of%20Auschwitz%E2%80%99.%20She%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20particularly%20sadistic%2C%20and%20is%20reported%20to%20have%20slept%20with%20and%2For%20raped%20prisoners%20(Laura%20Sjoberg%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20as%20Wartime%20Rapists%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20Grese%E2%80%99s%20sexuality%20was%20reported%20by%20Olga%20Lengyel%3A%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Griese%20woman%20was%20bisexual.%20My%20friend%2C%20who%20was%20her%20maid%2C%20informed%20me%20that%20Irma%20Griese%20frequently%20had%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%20relationships%20with%20inmates%20and%20then%20ordered%20the%20victims%20to%20the%20crematory.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20elsewhere%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIrma%20had%20seen%20this%20splendid%20specimen%20of%20manhood%2C%20the%20handsome%20Georgian%2C%20and%2C%20like%20some%20Eastern%20potentate%2C%20had%20picked%20him%20for%20herself.%20She%20had%20ordered%20him%20to%20her%20room.%20But%20when%20the%20proud%20young%20man%2C%20whose%20spirit%20had%20not%20been%20broken%20either%20by%20captivity%20or%20by%20Irma%E2%80%99s%20terrifying%20reputation%2C%20had%20refused%20to%20yield%20to%20her%20wishes%2C%20Irma%20had%20tried%20to%20force%20him%20to%20become%20her%20slave%20by%20compelling%20him%20to%20look%20on%20while%20she%20tortured%20the%20girl%20he%20loved.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20333px)%2085vw%2C%20333px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140459%2FIlse_Koch.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22333%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140459%2FIlse_Koch.png%20333w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140459%2FIlse_Koch-208x300.png%20208w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIlse%20Koch.%20Photo%3A%20Public%20domain%2FWikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIlse%20Koch%2C%20wife%20of%20the%20Buchenwald%20commandant%20Karl%20Koch%2C%20was%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeast%20of%20Buchenwald%E2%80%99%20and%20sometimes%20the%20%E2%80%98witch%20of%20Buchenwald%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMaria%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EMandl%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20famous%20for%20creating%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fholocaustmusic.ort.org%2Fplaces%2Fcamps%2Fdeath-camps%2Fauschwitz%2Fcamp-orchestras%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20Orchestra%20of%20Auschwitz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20played%20music%20during%20the%20sorting%20of%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20into%20%E2%80%98to%20be%20gassed%E2%80%99%20and%20those%20sent%20to%20labour%20%E2%80%93%20and%20during%20executions%2C%20was%20also%20called%20%E2%80%98The%20Beast%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHertha%20Bothe%20was%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Sadist%20of%20Stutthof%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Daniel%20Patrick%20Brown%20titled%20his%20study%20of%20Irme%20Grese%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%2Fabout%2FThe_Beautiful_Beast.html%3Fid%3D2V68uQEACAAJ%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Beautiful%20Beast%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Life%20and%20Crimes%20of%20SS-Aufseherin%20Irma%20Grese%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EDeborah%20Binz%2C%20the%20guard%20at%20Ravensbr%C3%BCck%2C%20was%20called%20a%20%E2%80%98demonic%20slut%E2%80%99.%20Carmen%20Maria%20Mory%20was%20%E2%80%98the%20devil%E2%80%99%20of%20Ravensbr%C3%BCck.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20animal%20trope%20employed%20contrasts%20with%20the%20attention%20paid%20to%20their%20appearance%20%E2%80%93%20beautiful%20but%20unrepentant%20in%20the%20court.%20Animalising%20the%20woman%20perpetrator%20enabled%20the%20legal%20and%20media%20representations%20to%20shift%20them%20into%20the%20realm%20of%20the%20subhuman.%20Through%20the%20use%20of%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%98witch%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98devil%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98demon%E2%80%99%20the%20discourse%20once%20again%20bestowed%20them%20with%20nonhuman%20traits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fhl%3Den%26lr%3D%26id%3DMdIEqP3sz6kC%26oi%3Dfnd%26pg%3DPR7%26dq%3DLaura%2BSjoberg%2Band%2BCaron%2BE.%2BGentry%26ots%3De630cb77w9%26sig%3D-7IBiyohmEco46MBq9n3vUfobRA%23v%3Donepage%26q%3DLaura%2520Sjoberg%2520and%2520Caron%2520E.%2520Gentry%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELaura%20Sjoberg%20and%20Caron%20E.%20Gentry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20their%20study%20of%20women%20perpetrators%20argue%20that%20media%20coverage%20and%20reportage%2C%20often%20even%20legal%20proceedings%2C%20employ%20three%20narratives.%20The%20women%20are%20mothers%2C%20monsters%20or%20whores%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mother%20narrative%20describes%20women%E2%80%99s%20violence%20as%20a%20need%20to%20belong%2C%20a%20need%20to%20nurture%2C%20and%20a%20way%20of%20taking%20care%20of%20and%20being%20loyal%20to%20men%3A%20motherhood%20gone%20awry.%20The%20monster%20narrative%20eliminates%20rational%20behaviour%2C%20ideological%20motivation%2C%20and%20culpability%20from%20women%20engaged%20in%20political%20violence.%20Instead%2C%20they%20describe%20violent%20women%20as%20insane%2C%20in%20denial%20of%20their%20femininity%2C%20no%20longer%20women%20or%20human.%20The%20whore%20narrative%20blames%20violence%20on%20the%20evils%20of%20female%20sexuality%20at%20its%20most%20intense%20or%20its%20most%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThomas%20Jardim%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hup.harvard.edu%2Fcatalog.php%3Fisbn%3D9780674249189%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIlse%20Koch%20on%20Trial%3A%20Making%20the%20%E2%80%9CBitch%20of%20Buchenwald%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20also%20notes%20that%20during%20the%20SS%20trial%20of%20Koch%2C%20her%20%E2%80%98character%E2%80%99%20was%20repeatedly%20underscored.%20Jardim%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20and%20German%20jurists%20alike%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20egregious%20crimes%20attributed%20to%20Koch%20were%20products%20of%20a%20deviant%20femininity%2C%20replete%20with%20perverse%20sexual%20impulses%20and%20a%20barbarism%20that%20placed%20her%20outside%20the%20community%20of%20%E2%80%9Cordinary%E2%80%9D%20women%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKoch%20was%20presented%20as%20%E2%80%98devoid%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%E2%80%9D%20feminine%20sensibilities.%20Irma%20Grese%20during%20her%20trial%20was%20the%20subject%20of%20considerable%20speculation%20regarding%20her%20femininity%20and%20sexuality.%20They%20were%20women%2C%20writes%20Jardim%2C%20whose%20%E2%80%98crimes%20were%20depicted%20as%20particularly%20abhorrent%20because%20they%20clashed%20with%20traditional%20norms%20of%20%E2%80%9Cwomanly%20behavior%E2%80%9D.%20Further%2C%20Koch%E2%80%99s%20supposed%20role%20as%20an%20active%20%E2%80%98participant%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Buchenwald%20crimes%20rested%20on%20hearsay%20evidence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20actions%20of%20the%20Nazi%20women%20were%20amplified%20as%20even%20more%20abhorrent%20than%20that%20of%20the%20hundreds%20of%20Nazi%20men%20%E2%80%93%20Karl%20Otto%20Koch%2C%20Ilse%E2%80%99s%20husband%2C%20was%20particularly%20brutal%2C%20as%20evidence%20shows%20%E2%80%93%20because%20it%20was%20unfeminine.%20They%20were%20not%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eordinary%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewomen%20because%20no%20ordinary%20woman%20could%20possibly%20do%20what%20they%20did.%20Thus%20Ilse%20Koch%20was%20supposed%20to%20have%20had%20prisoners%20executed%20so%20that%20their%20skin%20could%20be%20used%20to%20make%20lampshades%20for%20her%20home%2C%20which%20was%20next%20to%20the%20camp.%20Such%20absolute%20heights%20of%20deviant%20femininity%20became%20the%20stuff%20of%20media%20outrage%2C%20as%20Anthony%20Rowland%20notes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scandalised%20narrative%20of%20female%20perpetrators%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20(again%2C%20invisible)%20men%20in%20the%20pathology%20lab%20might%20have%20created%20the%20lampshade%20is%20of%20no%20interest.%20The%20perceived%20perversion%20of%20female%20masculinity%20allows%20for%20a%20much%20more%20convenient%20explanation%20of%20atavism%20and%20(male)%20masculine%20aberrance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20attention%20was%20focused%20on%20the%20violation%20of%20gender%20norms%20in%20situations%20of%20political%20and%20mass%20violence.%20As%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Ficla%2F15%2F2%2Farticle-p207_1.xml%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520explorative%2520study%2520however%252C%2520shows%2Cinvolved%2520in%2520mass%2520atroci%2520ties.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlette%20Smeulers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20summarises%20it%2C%20%E2%80%98women%20who%20transgress%20the%20female%20stereotypes%20more%20than%20men%20do%20and%20are%20therefore%20more%20often%20considered%20as%20%E2%80%98deviant%20and%20unnatural%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20other%20factors%20too%2C%20especially%20in%20high-profile%20trials%20like%20Koch%E2%80%99s.%20Evidence%20by%20other%20SS%20wives%20was%20collected%20and%20presented%20in%20the%20court.%20The%20%E2%80%98evidence%E2%80%99%20also%20highlighted%20her%20%E2%80%98reputation%E2%80%99.%20Anna%20Reimer%20deposed%3A%20%E2%80%98On%20the%20other%20hand%20it%20was%20not%20unknown%20to%20me%20and%20also%20to%20my%20women%20comrades%20%E2%80%A6that%20Frau%20Koch%20already%20had%20a%20bad%20reputation%20as%20a%20woman%20at%20that%20time%E2%80%99.%20That%20is%2C%20a%20set%20of%20norms%20subscribed%20to%20by%20the%20inmates%2C%20the%20SS%20wives%20and%20the%20later-day%20commentators%20inscribed%20a%20certain%20%E2%80%98reputation%E2%80%99%20upon%20Koch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20such%20acts%20of%20mass%20violence%20or%20genocide%20are%20constructed%20in%20public%2C%20including%20legal%2C%20discourse%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98repertoire%20of%20behaviours%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20the%20phrase%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fgh%2Farticle-abstract%2F19%2F3%2F369%2F680819%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%26login%3Dfalse%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlexandra%20Przyrembel%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20her%20study%20of%20Ilse%20Koch%20%E2%80%93%20are%20woven%20into%20it%2C%20a%20repertoire%20that%20is%20determined%20by%20prevalent%20social%20codes%20regarding%20gender%2C%20and%20from%20which%20we%20cannot%20separate%20how%20we%20are%20shown%2C%20understand%20and%20consume%20a%20Koch%20or%20a%20Grese.%20Thus%20women%E2%80%99s%20crimes%20in%20the%20camps%20become%20more%20pathologised%20than%20that%20of%20men%3A%20they%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98normal%20women%E2%80%99%20at%20all.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20women%20were%20implicated%2C%20indisputably%20so%2C%20in%20political%20violence%2C%20they%20have%20been%20consigned%20to%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98deviant%E2%80%99%20humanity%2C%20while%20the%20male%20perpetrators%20remain%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20humanity%2C%20but%20as%20vile%20examples%20of%20it.%20This%20is%20so%20because%2C%20as%20the%20trials%20and%20media%20coverage%20of%20Nazi%20women%20shows%2C%20violence%20and%20even%20cruelty%20is%20seen%20and%20believed%20to%20be%20integral%20to%20the%20masculine.%20How%20many%20times%20have%20we%20heard%20rapists%20and%20molesters%20being%20explained%20away%20as%20%E2%80%98boys%20will%20be%20boys%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Does%20atrocity%20have%20a%20gender%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBarbara%20Ehreinrich%2C%20pained%20by%20the%20images%20of%20Lynndie%20England%2C%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-2004-may-16-op-ehrenreich16-story.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Feminism%E2%80%99s%20Assumptions%20Upended%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20mourned%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20certain%20kind%20of%20feminism%2C%20or%20perhaps%20I%20should%20say%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20feminist%20naivete%2C%20died%20in%20Abu%20Ghraib.%20It%20was%20a%20feminism%20that%20saw%20men%20as%20the%20perpetual%20perpetrators%2C%20women%20as%20the%20perpetual%20victims%20and%20male%20sexual%20violence%20against%20women%20as%20the%20root%20of%20all%20injustice.%20Rape%20has%20repeatedly%20been%20an%20instrument%20of%20war%20and%2C%20to%20some%20feminists%2C%20it%20was%20beginning%20to%20look%20as%20if%20war%20was%20an%20extension%20of%20rape.%20There%20seemed%20to%20be%20at%20least%20some%20evidence%20that%20male%20sexual%20sadism%20was%20connected%20to%20our%20species%E2%80%99%20tragic%20propensity%20for%20violence.%20That%20was%20before%20we%20had%20seen%20female%20sexual%20sadism%20in%20action.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20locate%20England%20within%20a%20context%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20we%20have%20learned%20from%20Abu%20Ghraib%2C%20once%20and%20for%20all%2C%20is%20that%20a%20uterus%20is%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20a%20conscience%E2%80%A6%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20do%20not%20change%20institutions%20simply%20by%20assimilating%20into%20them%2C%20only%20by%20consciously%20deciding%20to%20fight%20for%20change.%20We%20need%20a%20feminism%20that%20teaches%20a%20woman%20to%20say%20no%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20to%20the%20date%20rapist%20or%20overly%20insistent%20boyfriend%20but%2C%20when%20necessary%2C%20to%20the%20military%20or%20corporate%20hierarchy%20within%20which%20she%20finds%20herself%20%E2%80%A6%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20be%20equal%20to%20men%2C%20when%20the%20men%20are%20acting%20like%20beasts.%20It%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20assimilate.%20We%20need%20to%20create%20a%20world%20worth%20assimilating%20into.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08142835%2FFrFPL33XwAAECnu.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22685%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08142835%2FFrFPL33XwAAECnu.png%20685w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08142835%2FFrFPL33XwAAECnu-300x205.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667165%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22467%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELynndie%20England%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40Thatsenough0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEhreinrich%E2%80%99s%20finger%20points%20to%20institutional%20requirements%20of%20men%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20women%2C%20especially%20in%20fields%20like%20the%20military.%20While%20she%20does%20not%20absolve%20England%2C%20she%20notes%20that%20a%20culture%20that%20endorses%20(masculine)%20violence%20also%20implies%20that%20those%20who%20assimilate%20into%20the%20culture%2C%20begin%20to%20embody%20those%20same%20values.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20should%20be%20remembered%20that%20the%20Nazi%20camps%20were%20places%20where%20no%20known%20laws%20applied%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%98absolute%20state%20of%20exception%E2%80%99%20as%20Giorgio%20Agamben%20termed%20it%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20and%20terror%20was%20the%20sole%20normative%20order%20of%20the%20day%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20treatment%20of%20prisoners.%20The%20camp%20was%20an%20instantiation%20of%20the%20genocidal%20state%2C%20its%20justification.%20In%20this%20genocidal%20state%20it%20was%20the%20already%20circulating%20ethnic%20hatred%20that%20enabled%2C%20welcomed%20and%20operated%20the%20camps.%20And%20this%20did%20not%20need%20a%20gender%2C%20it%20assimilated%20all%20genders%20to%20itself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20commentators%20who%20have%20examined%20the%20cultural%20representations%20of%20female%20perpetrators%20also%20echo%20Ehreinrich.%20Susannah%20Heschel%20ponders%20there%20is%20a%20widely%20shared%20assumption%20that%20men%E2%80%99s%20cruelty%20is%2C%20in%20part%2C%20an%20expression%20of%20%E2%80%98masculinity%2C%20but%20no%20exploration%20into%20whether%20women%E2%80%99s%20acts%20of%20cruelty%20are%20linked%20to%20expressions%20of%20their%20femininity%2C%20understanding%20both%20terms%20as%20social%20constructs.%20The%20realm%20of%20the%20camp%20belonged%20to%20the%20SS%2C%20a%20male%20organisation.%20Did%20women%20guards%20join%20the%20realm%20of%20power%20reserved%20for%20the%20SS%2C%20or%20transgress%20it%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWendy%20Lower%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20young%20women%2C%20the%20possibilities%20for%20advancement%20lay%20in%20the%20emerging%20Nazi%20empire%20abroad.%20They%20left%20behind%20repressive%20laws%2C%20bourgeois%20mores%2C%20and%20social%20traditions%20that%20made%20life%20in%20Germany%20regimented%20and%20oppressive.%20Women%20in%20the%20eastern%20territories%20witnessed%20and%20committed%20atrocities%20in%20a%20more%20open%20system%2C%20and%20as%20part%20of%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20a%20professional%20opportunity%20and%20a%20liberating%20experience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDeviant%20femininity%20and%20typical%20masculinity%20do%20not%20suffice%20as%20frames%20to%20%E2%80%98read%E2%80%99%20either%20Irma%20Grese%20or%20Rudolf%20H%C3%B6ss%20(the%20Auschwitz%20commandant)%2C%20but%20the%20social%2C%20cultural%20norms%20of%20the%20camp%20that%20constructed%20specific%20models%20of%20behaviour%2C%20encouraged%20certain%20others%20%E2%80%93%20for%20privilege%20and%20power%2C%20career%20and%20companionship%20%E2%80%93%20among%20both%20men%20and%20women.%20An%20entire%20generation%20of%20men%20and%20women%20were%20%E2%80%98lost%E2%80%99%20to%20Nazi%20ideology%2C%20and%20they%20gained%20careers%20and%20wealth%20when%20they%20were%20thus%20lost.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20did%20the%20camp%20structure%20and%20operations%20of%20power%20draw%20people%20in%20as%20guards%20and%20encourage%20them%20to%20grow%20into%20torturers%3F%20We%20find%20some%20cues%20in%20Sarah%20Helm%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%2Fabout%2FIf_this_is_a_Woman.html%3Fid%3D4-cvnwEACAAJ%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20This%20Is%20A%20Woman%3A%20Inside%20Ravensbr%C3%BCck%3A%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20Concentration%20Camp%20for%20Women%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewhere%20she%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%98Binz%E2%80%99s%20appetite%20for%20cruelty%20soon%20made%20an%20impression%20on%20everyone%20in%20the%20camp.%20And%20yet%2C%20until%20she%20got%20the%20job%20here%2C%20she%20had%20been%20little%20noticed%E2%80%99.%20Helm%20adds%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20daughter%20of%20a%20forester%2C%20Dorothea%20Binz%20was%20one%20of%20several%20local%20girls%20who%20started%20work%20over%20the%20summer.%20These%20recruits%20were%20different%20to%20the%20women%20who%20arrived%20with%20the%20prisoners%20five%20months%20earlier%20%E2%80%A6%20They%20had%20no%20experience%20of%20any%20other%20penal%20institution%2C%20and%20many%20were%20so%20young%20that%20they%20had%20no%20meaningful%20experience%20of%20life%20before%20Nazi%20rule.%20Work%20at%20the%20camp%20was%20their%20first%20job.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20about%20another%20guard%2C%20she%20writes%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELangefeld%20had%20been%20as%20eager%20as%20anyone%20to%20fulfil%20Himmler%E2%80%99s%20edict%20on%20%E2%80%98protecting%20the%20homeland%20from%20internal%20enemies%E2%80%99.%20The%20mere%20sight%20of%20women%20standing%20for%20hours%20in%20the%20cold%20and%20wet%20demonstrated%20her%20iron%20discipline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20no%20prehistory%20of%20violence%2C%20placed%20in%20a%20context%20where%20power%20was%20more%20or%20less%20unlimited%2C%20aspiring%20to%20greater%20and%20better%20careers%2C%20the%20men%2C%20and%20women%2C%20in%20the%20camp%20order%20quickly%20assimilated%20the%20norms%20of%20torture%2C%20beating%20and%20execution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECultures%20of%20violence%2C%20such%20as%20made%20Nazi%20Germany%20a%20genocidal%20state%2C%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20perpetrators%20to%20emerge%20even%20though%20not%20all%20ordinary%20men%2C%20and%20women%2C%20become%20genocidal.%20Christopher%20Browning%20asks%20a%20goose-bump%20inducing%20question%20in%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goodreads.com%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F647492.Ordinary_Men%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOrdinary%20Men%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20%E2%80%98If%20the%20men%20of%20Reserve%20Police%20Battalion%20101%20could%20become%20killers%20under%20such%20circumstances%2C%20what%20group%20of%20men%20cannot%3F%E2%80%99%20If%20we%20broaden%20the%20ambit%20of%20Browning%E2%80%99s%20question%2C%20we%20have%20an%20answer%20to%20Susannah%20Heschel%E2%80%99s%20question%20on%20atrocity%E2%80%99s%20gender.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EImpunity%20and%20immunity%2C%20both%20bestowed%20by%20the%20structures%20of%20power%20and%20cultural%20norms%20open%20up%20the%20field%20of%20violent%20action%2C%20and%20players%20seeking%20to%20at%20least%20enter%20the%20field%20of%20play%20need%20to%20first%20sign%20up%2C%20tacitly%20endorsing%20the%20(violent)%20culture%20of%20the%20field.%20When%20we%20make%20a%20genocidal%20state%2C%20there%20will%20be%20demands%20to%20enrol%20as%20citizens%20by%20meeting%20citizenship%20requirements%20of%20ideology%2C%20hate%20and%20war-mongering.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20absurd%20to%20ask%2C%20as%20Nazi%20Germany%20shows%2C%20which%20gender%20dominates%20the%20genocidal%20state.%20It%20is%20enough%20that%20such%20a%20state%20exists.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBuild%20a%20genocidal%20state%20and%20camps%20will%20emerge.%20Build%20a%20genocidal%20state%20and%20there%20will%20be%20men%2C%20and%20women%2C%20to%20run%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpramod-k-nayar%5C%22%3EPramod%20K.%20Nayar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691505007000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08144406%2F187141eb-5424-463f-be84-499b1480aeb0.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgender%2Fgenders-of-atrocity-before-lynndie-england-there-was-ilse-koch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20absurd%20to%20ask%20which%20gender%20dominates%20the%20genocidal%20state.%20Build%20a%20genocidal%20state%20and%20there%20will%20be%20men%2C%20and%20women%2C%20to%20run%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgender%2Fgenders-of-atrocity-before-lynndie-england-there-was-ilse-koch%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Motorcyclist%20captured%20driving%20through%20po