Cp%3EThese%20trends%20concern%20corporate%20India%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20they%20point%20towards%20an%20increasing%20risk%20of%20violent%20conflicts%20in%20the%20country.%20In%20the%20worst%20case%2C%20such%20acts%20of%20violence%20could%20culminate%20into%20a%20genocide%2C%20which%20would%20annihilate%20the%20social%20fabric%20as%20well%20as%20the%20economy%20of%20the%20country%2C%20casting%20a%20long%20dark%20shadow%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20future.%20Corporate%20India%2C%20which%20hopes%20to%20reach%20new%20frontiers%20of%20international%20growth%20and%20innovation%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20cannot%20afford%20to%20live%20with%20even%20a%20small%20possibility%20of%20such%20a%20scenario%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20letter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20signatories%20said%20that%20because%20India%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20tolerance%20and%20peaceful%20coexistence%20of%20different%20faiths%2C%20they%20would%20like%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20large-scale%20violent%20conflicts%20or%20genocide%20in%20India%20is%20still%20small.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20this%20risk%20is%20no%20longer%20close%20to%20zero%2C%20as%20the%20rapidly%20increasing%20levels%20of%20radicalization%20of%20citizens%20are%20fermenting%20an%20atmosphere%20conducive%20to%20large-scale%20violence%20being%20triggered%20due%20to%20unexpected%20disturbances%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeaders%20of%20corporate%20India%20have%20an%20important%20and%20substantial%20role%20to%20play%20in%20curbing%20the%20spread%20of%20hate%20and%20misinformation%2C%20the%20letter%20said%2C%20asking%20corporates%20to%20%E2%80%98Stop%20Funding%20Hate%E2%80%99%3B%20%E2%80%98Support%20Responsible%20Stakeholders%E2%80%99%3B%20%E2%80%98Curate%20a%20Welcoming%20Work%20Culture%E2%80%99%3B%20and%20%E2%80%98Use%20Your%20Voice%20for%20Fraternity%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statement%2C%20and%20the%20list%20of%20signatories%2C%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E