%80%99%20into%20oblivion.%20They%20care%20a%20damn%20that%20every%20morning%20new%20sorrows%20strike%20Indians%20in%20the%20face.%20We%20bear%20witness%20to%20bloodletting%2C%20to%20rapes%2C%20and%20to%20the%20terrible%20spectacle%20of%20mobs%20stripping%20women%20of%20their%20dignity%20and%20bodily%20integrity.%20We%20see%20in%20despair%20blood-spattered%20desolate%20regions%20of%20the%20country.%20How%20much%20blood%20is%20going%20to%20be%20spilt%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20the%20country%3F%20What%20has%20happened%20to%20us%20as%20a%20people%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EYeh%20kahan%20aa%20gaye%20hum%2C%20yuhi%20saath%20chalte%20chalte%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20to%20suggest%20that%20India%20is%20a%20stranger%20to%20communal%20and%20caste%20violence.%20Ahmedabad%20(1969)%2C%20Belchi%20(1978)%2C%20Delhi%20(1984)%20Bombay%20(1993)%2C%20Bathan%20Tola%20(1996)%2C%20Laxman%20Bathe%20(1997)%2C%20Gujarat%20(2002)%2C%20Kherlainji%20(2000)%2C%20Dharampuri%20(2012)%20and%20Muzzafarnagar%20(2013)%20are%20not%20only%20names%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20maps%2C%20they%20tell%20stories%20of%20shameful%20incidents%20in%20our%20postcolonial%20history%2C%20of%20inhuman%20acts%20performed%20by%20one%20human%20being%20on%20another%20for%20reasons%20outside%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20control%2C%20birth%20into%20a%20religious%20or%20caste%20group%20that%20has%20been%20stereotyped%20as%20the%20enemy%20or%20as%20inferior.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20violence%20has%20become%20part%20of%20the%20political%20process.%20It%20plays%20itself%20out%20in%20tragic%20ways%2C%20sometimes%20as%20individual%20acts%20of%20cold-blooded%20murder%2C%20sometimes%20as%20despicable%20collective%20acts%20performed%20on%20the%20bodies%20of%20minorities%2C%20sometimes%20as%20hate%20speech%20that%20encourages%20listeners%20to%20kill%2C%20loot%2C%20and%20rape%2C%20sometimes%20as%20justification%20of%20harm%20done%20to%20our%20body%20politic%2C%20and%20almost%20always%20as%20silence%20by%20people%20who%20can%20make%20a%20difference.%20One%20statement%20by%20a%20charismatic%20political%20figure%20who%20says%20firmly%2C%20%E2%80%9CEnough%2C%20no%20more%20bloodshed%2C%E2%80%9D%20can%20end%20this%20terrible%20cycle%20of%20violence.%20After%20all%2C%20such%20statements%20have%20succeeded%20in%20ending%20violence%20in%20history%2C%20at%20least%20for%20long%20periods.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08112954%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-08-at-11.17.10-AM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08112954%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-08-at-11.17.10-AM.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08112954%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-08-at-11.17.10-AM-300x169.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667089%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESeveral%20shanties%20have%20been%20vacated%20by%20Muslims%20in%20the%20Nuh%20region%20over%20the%20last%20week%20because%20of%20rioting.%20Photo%3A%20Tarushi%20Aswani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMandela%3A%20Peace%20as%20reconciliation%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20example%20of%20Nelson%20Mandela%20comes%20to%20mind.%20As%20the%20date%20of%20his%20release%20after%2027%20years%20in%20the%20inhuman%20prison%20system%20of%20Apartheid%20South%20Africa%20came%20nearer%2C%20Mandela%20was%20beset%20with%20considerable%20doubt.%20After%20he%20had%20been%20jailed%20in%201962%2C%20South%20Africa%20had%20been%20trapped%20in%20a%20whirlwind%20of%20violence.%20Mandela%20knew%20that%20the%20moment%20of%20his%20release%20would%20signify%20the%20readiness%20of%20the%20Apartheid%20regime%20to%20transfer%20power%20to%20the%20majority%20and%20that%20this%20would%20unleash%20another%20round%20of%20violence.%20The%20recognition%20changed%20his%20attitude%20towards%20politics.%20From%20a%20man%20who%20had%20founded%20the%20militant%20organisation%20uMkhonto%20we%20Sizwe%20(Spear%20of%20the%20Nation)%2C%20the%20armed%20wing%20of%20the%20African%20Nationalist%20Congress%20(ANC)%2C%20Mandela%20adopted%20the%20ideal%20of%20peace%20through%20reconciliation.%20He%20realised%20that%20peace%20and%20reconciliation%20were%20essential%20preconditions%20of%20democracy.%20Lesser%20men%20might%20have%20advocated%20that%20Black%20South%20Africans%20were%20now%20in%20a%20position%20to%20wreak%20vengeance%20on%20the%20White%20community%20for%20historical%20injustice.%20Not%20Mandela.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20February%2011%2C%201990%2C%20Mandela%20walked%20out%20of%20prison.%20The%20road%20from%20his%20prison%20to%20his%20home%20was%20lined%20with%20a%20boundless%20sea%20of%20people%2C%20cheering%2C%20holding%20flags%20and%20banners%2C%20clapping%2C%20dancing%20and%20laughing.%20Addressing%20enthusiastic%20crowds%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFriends%2C%20comrades%20and%20fellow%20South%20Africans%2C%20I%20greet%20you%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20peace%2C%20democracy%20and%20freedom%20for%20all!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFreedom%20for%20all%20was%20to%20become%20his%20mantra%20for%20a%20democratic%20and%20inclusive%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20was%20an%20indication%20of%20his%20path%20to%20an%20inclusive%20democracy.%20The%20question%20that%20occupied%20him%20was%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20India%20confronts.%20How%20do%20we%20live%20out%20our%20lives%20with%20those%20that%20ruled%20us%2C%20sometimes%2C%20unjustly%20in%20the%20past%3F%20Do%20we%20exact%20vengeance%2C%20and%20get%20caught%20up%20in%20an%20endless%20spiral%20of%20revenge%3F%20Or%20do%20we%20learn%20to%20accept%20history%20and%20focus%20on%20moving%20together%20towards%20an%20inclusive%20democracy%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20a%20press%20conference%20held%20after%20his%20release%2C%20Mandela%20gave%20us%20the%20answer%20to%20these%20questions.%20His%20formulation%20resonated%20with%20generosity%2C%20forethought%20and%20cool%2C%20sane%20politics.%20He%20did%20not%20want%20the%20White%20community%20to%20be%20driven%20away%2C%20this%20would%20devastate%20the%20country.%20Whites%2C%20he%20said%2C%20were%20fellow%20South%20Africans%20and%20anyone%20who%20abandoned%20Apartheid%20had%20a%20place%20in%20a%20democratic%20South%20Africa.%20Black%20Africans%20had%20to%20learn%20to%20live%20with%20their%20erstwhile%20oppressors.%20Whites%20had%20to%20give%20up%20the%20dream%2C%20espoused%20by%20many%2C%20that%20they%20are%20given%20a%20separate%20state.%20Mandela%20was%20prescient.%20Secession%20or%20partition%20of%20territory%20is%20a%20relatively%20easy%20option.%20What%20is%20more%20difficult%20is%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20give%20up%20violence%20and%20learn%20to%20live%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETowards%20this%20end%2C%20Mandela%20believed%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Frantz%20Fanon%20had%20theorised%20earlier%20%E2%80%93%20that%20violence%20destroys%20both%20the%20victim%20and%20the%20perpetrator.%20He%20knew%20that%20for%20democracy%20to%20succeed%2C%20both%20the%20oppressor%20and%20the%20oppressed%20had%20to%20be%20liberated%20from%20the%20chains%20that%20violence%20had%20bound%20them%20with.%20In%201994%2C%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20man%20who%20takes%20away%20another%20man%E2%80%99s%20freedom%20is%20a%20prisoner%20of%20hatred%3B%20he%20is%20locked%20behind%20the%20bars%20of%20prejudice%20and%20narrow-mindedness.%20I%20am%20not%20truly%20free%20if%20I%20am%20taking%20away%20someone%20else%E2%80%99s%20freedom%E2%80%A6The%20oppressor%20and%20the%20oppressed%20alike%20are%20robbed%20of%20their%20humanity.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20subsequent%20speeches%20also%20taught%20us%20that%20the%20problems%20of%20the%20human%20condition%20cannot%20be%20resolved%20in%20one%20go.%20These%20problems%2C%20as%20well%20as%20new%20ones%2C%20are%20bound%20to%20be%20produced%20and%20reproduced.%20Politics%20offers%20no%20resolutions.%20All%20it%20can%20do%20is%20resolve%20dilemmas%20%E2%80%93%20given%20imagination%2C%20generosity%2C%20patience%2C%20resourcefulness%20and%20courage.%20Violence%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20proliferates%20like%20the%20proverbial%20amoeba.%20It%20gives%20us%20nothing%20but%20death%20and%20destruction.%20Violence%20is%20barren%3B%20it%20can%20only%20produce%20arid%20landscapes%20of%20human%20suffering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20lesson%20Mandela%20taught%20us%20is%20that%20the%20human%20condition%20is%20frail%20and%20ambiguous.%20No%20one%20is%20perfect%2C%20all%20human%20beings%20are%20flawed.%20We%20are%20as%20flawed%20as%20the%20people%20we%20inflict%20violence%20on.%20That%20is%20why%20he%20forgave%20his%20jailors.%20He%20believed%20that%20people%20often%20act%20violently%20because%20they%20are%20unthinkingly%20imbricated%20in%20ideologies%20that%20are%20far%20removed%20from%20humanity.%20Though%20his%20jailors%20in%20the%20three%20jails%20he%20had%20been%20imprisoned%20in%20were%20Afrikaaners%2C%20Mandela%20recognised%20that%20their%20sensibilities%20of%20%E2%80%9Cother%E2%80%9D%20human%20beings%20are%20shaped%20by%20ideologies%20of%20hatred%20that%20legitimise%20state%20power.%20He%20in%20effect%20reiterated%20a%20well-known%20axiom%20of%20political%20science.%20The%20state%20of%20politics%20in%20a%20society%20depends%20upon%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20way%20in%20which%20these%20flaws%20can%20be%20remedied%20is%20by%20compassion.%20Leaders%20who%20set%20agendas%20have%20to%20transcend%20petty%20vindictiveness.%20They%20have%20to%20abandon%20the%20conviction%20that%20the%20past%20is%20so%20important%20that%20it%20has%20to%20shape%20our%20present%20or%20encourage%20people%20to%20do%20so.%20We%20have%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20history%2C%20not%20replicate%20it.%20Mandela%20stood%20out%20among%20his%20contemporaries%20because%20he%20reversed%20the%20principle%20of%20justice%20established%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalww2museum.org%2Fwar%2Ftopics%2Fnuremberg-trials%5C%22%3ENuremberg%20trials%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20that%20a%20just%20order%20is%20based%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctooth%20for%20a%20tooth%20and%20an%20eye%20for%20an%20eye%E2%80%9D.%20He%20did%20not%20believe%20in%20victor%E2%80%99s%20justice%2C%20he%20believed%20that%20people%20can%20only%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20history%20through%20compassion%2C%20forgiveness%20and%20empathy%20inspired%20by%20leaders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftruth-and-reconciliation-in-india%5C%22%3EWhy%20India%20Needs%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20practice%20of%20reconciliation%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201994%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20history%20of%20South%20Africa%2C%20all%20races%20voted%20in%20the%20general%20elections.%20The%20turnout%20was%20massive%20and%20the%20ANC%20won%2062%25%20of%20the%20seats.%20Mandela%20was%20elected%20president%20and%20he%20proceeded%20to%20establish%20a%20multi-cultural%20cabinet.%20The%20last%20head%20of%20state%20of%20the%20apartheid%20regime%2C%20Frederik%20Willem%20de%20Klerk%2C%20was%20appointed%20as%20one%20of%20the%20many%20deputy%20presidents.%20The%20new%20president%20of%20South%20Africa%20began%20to%20walk%20the%20path%20of%20reconciliation%2C%20from%20fashioning%20a%20new%20anthem%20as%20an%20amalgam%20of%20the%20old%20and%20the%20new%20to%20forging%20a%20multi-racial%20team%20for%20the%20Rugby%20World%20Cup%20finals%20held%20in%20the%20country%20in%201995.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140127%2FFrederik_de_Klerk_with_Nelson_Mandela_-_World_Economic_Forum_Annual_Meeting_Davos_1992.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140127%2FFrederik_de_Klerk_with_Nelson_Mandela_-_World_Economic_Forum_Annual_Meeting_Davos_1992.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140127%2FFrederik_de_Klerk_with_Nelson_Mandela_-_World_Economic_Forum_Annual_Meeting_Davos_1992-300x234.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667150%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22625%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EF.W.%20de%20Klerk%20and%20Nelson%20Mandela.%20Photo%3A%20World%20Economic%20Forum%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20initiative%20was%20wonderfully%20captured%20by%20the%20movie%20%3Cem%3EInvictus%3C%2Fem%3E%20directed%20by%20Clint%20Eastwood%20with%20Morgan%20Freeman%20playing%20Mandela%2C%20and%20Matt%20Damon%20as%20the%20white%20captain%20of%20the%20rugby%20team%2C%20Francois%20Pienaar.%20When%20the%20South%20African%20team%20won%2C%20people%20erupted%20in%20joy.%20The%20white%20singer%20P.J.%20Powers%20wrote%20lyrics%20that%20resounded%20with%20the%20official%20slogan%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98One%20team%2C%20one%20country%2F%20Gathering%20together%2FOne%20mind%2C%20one%20heart%2FEvery%20creed%2C%20every%20colour%20%2FOnce%20joined%2C%20never%20apart.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMandela%20is%20remembered%20for%20three%20marvellous%20speeches%20that%20resonated%20with%20his%20conviction%20that%20reconciliation%20was%20the%20only%20route%20to%20peace.%20On%20his%20release%2C%20he%20promised%20all%20inhabitants%20equality%20of%20opportunity.%20The%20second%20speech%20was%20given%20when%20one%20of%20the%20most%20loved%20leaders%20of%20the%20ANC%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomalley.nelsonmandela.org%2Findex.php%2Fsite%2Fq%2F03lv02424%2F04lv03370%2F05lv03422.htm%5C%22%3EChris%20Hani%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20murdered%20by%20a%20white%20Polish%20racist%20Janusz%20Walu%C5%9B%20on%20April%2010%2C%201995.%20The%20country%20could%20have%20been%20destroyed%20by%20racial%20violence.%20But%20when%20Mandela%20spoke%20on%20South%20Africa%20Broadcasting%20Corporation%20television%2C%20he%20changed%20the%20narrative.%20%E2%80%9CA%20white%20man%20full%20of%20prejudice%20and%20hate%2C%20came%20to%20our%20country%20and%20committed%20a%20deed%20so%20foul%20that%20our%20whole%20nation%20now%20teeters%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20disaster.%20A%20white%20woman%20of%20Afrikaner%20origin%20risked%20her%20life%20so%20that%20we%20may%20know%20and%20bring%20to%20justice%2C%20this%20assassin.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHuman%20nature%2C%20Mandela%20taught%20us%2C%20cannot%20be%20essentialised%20in%20terms%20of%20race.%20All%20races%20grieved%20when%20Hani%20was%20murdered.%20It%20is%20this%20unifying%20sentiment%20that%20constitutes%20a%20common%20humanity%20and%20common%20ends%2C%20particularly%20the%20end%20to%20unite%20against%20the%20forces%20of%20hatred.%20This%2C%20he%20said%20in%20his%20speech%2C%20is%20a%20watershed%20moment%20for%20us%2C%20and%20our%20decisions%20and%20actions%20will%20determine%20whether%20we%20can%20move%20together%20to%20elect%20a%20democratic%20government.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20must%20not%20let%20the%20men%20who%20worship%20war%2C%20and%20who%20lust%20after%20blood%2C%20precipitate%20actions%20that%20will%20plunge%20our%20country%20into%20another%20Angola.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMandela%20was%20committed%20to%20the%20project%20of%20unearthing%20not%20differences%20but%20commonalities%20between%20people%2C%20and%20to%20the%20project%20of%20inspiring%20them%20to%20accept%20history%20and%20move%20forward.%20When%20he%20won%20the%201995%20election%2C%20he%20made%20another%20inspiring%20speech%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20stand%20before%20you%20filled%20with%20deep%20pride%20and%20joy%E2%80%A6It%20is%20not%20the%20individuals%20that%20matter%2C%20but%20the%20collective%E2%80%A6%20This%20is%20the%20time%20to%20heal%20new%20wounds%20and%20build%20a%20new%20South%20Africa.%E2%80%9D%20The%20notion%20of%20peace%20through%20reconciliation%20was%20institutionalised%20in%20the%20South%20African%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FTruth-and-Reconciliation-Commission-South-Africa%5C%22%3ETruth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20may%20not%20have%20achieved%20much%20in%20the%20way%20of%20remedial%20justice%2C%20but%20it%20did%20manage%20to%20make%20people%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20history%20of%20oppression.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fremembering-nelson-mandela-july-18%5C%22%3ERemembering%20Nelson%20Mandela%2C%20Who%20Honoured%20the%20Power%20of%20Reconciliation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EComing%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20past%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20does%20it%20mean%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F030642209602500522%5C%22%3Easks%3C%2Fa%3E%20Michael%20Ignatieff%2C%20for%20a%20nation%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20its%20past%3F%20%E2%80%9CCan%20a%20nation%E2%80%99s%20past%20make%20people%20ill%20as%20we%20know%20repressed%20memories%20sometimes%20make%20individuals%20ill.%20Conversely%2C%20can%20a%20nation%20or%20contending%20parts%20of%20it%20be%20reconciled%20to%20its%20past%20as%20individuals%20can%2C%20by%20replacing%20myth%20with%20fact%20and%20lies%20with%20truth%3F%E2%80%9D%20Can%20nations%20%E2%80%98come%20awake%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20nightmare%20of%20the%20past%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20Plato%20to%20John%20Rawls%2C%20political%20theory%20has%20been%20concerned%20with%20creating%20a%20perfectly%20just%20society.%20Today%2C%20the%20agenda%20of%20political%20theorists%20has%20been%20curtailed%20by%20another%2C%20more%20urgent%2C%20question.%20How%20do%20societies%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20their%20history%20of%20conflict%3F%20How%20do%20people%20learn%20to%20live%20together%3F%20As%20a%20start%2C%20the%20past%2C%20howsoever%20harrowing%20it%20may%20be%2C%20cannot%20be%20forgotten%20or%20set%20aside.%20We%20must%20know%20which%20valley%20we%20have%20walked%20through%2C%20which%20mountains%20we%20have%20climbed%2C%20which%20thicket%20we%20have%20cleared%2C%20which%20paths%20have%20we%20traversed%2C%20and%20what%20confronted%20us%20on%20the%20way.%20Forgetting%20is%20not%20an%20option%20if%20we%20have%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20our%20present.%20We%20have%20to%20recognise%20that%20traumas%20that%20have%20been%20suppressed%20will%20re-emerge%20in%20destructive%20ways.%20Societies%20that%20cannot%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20past%20are%20fragile.%20They%20can%20burst%20asunder%20at%20the%20slightest%20pretext.%20A%20mere%20spark%20is%20enough%20to%20set%20off%20a%20conflagration.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20we%20must%20learn%20from%20history%20%E2%80%93%20not%20replicate%20historical%20injustice.%20Witness%20the%20tragedy%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20life.%20If%20past%20rulers%20of%20India%20broke%20temples%2C%20today%20we%20bring%20down%20mosques.%20What%20have%20we%20learned%20from%20history%3F%20History%20is%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20past%20and%20to%20the%20future%2C%20but%20we%20cannot%20be%20held%20captive%20to%20its%20ruthless%20dynamics.%20Historical%20memories%20have%20to%20teach%20us%20wisdom%20not%20inspire%20us%20to%20loot%2C%20burn%2C%20and%20kill.%20We%20have%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20history%2C%20with%20the%20realisation%20that%20terrible%20things%20were%20done%20by%20people%20to%20other%20people%2C%20and%20pledge%20that%20we%20will%20not%20reproduce%20historical%20harm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20we%20cannot%20hold%20our%20own%20people%20responsible%20for%20what%20rulers%2C%20who%20happened%20to%20belong%20to%20their%20religion%2C%20did%20in%20the%20past.%20We%2C%20taking%20inspiration%20from%20leaders%20who%20were%20larger%20than%20others%2C%20as%20Mandela%20was%2C%20have%20to%20learn%20compassion%2C%20we%20must%20approach%20collective%20life%20with%20a%20spirit%20of%20generosity%20and%20kindness.%20In%20turn%2C%20leaders%20who%20rule%20must%20recognise%20their%20obligation%20to%20inspire%20societies%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20a%20troubled%20past%20not%20play%20it%20up.%20They%20have%20to%20set%20an%20example.%20It%20is%20precisely%20here%20that%20reconciliation%20makes%20its%20appearance.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20the%20perfect%20solution%20but%20it%20might%20just%20change%20our%20attitude%20to%20the%20past.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20we%20have%20to%20learn%20from%20Mandela%20that%20peace%20is%20not%20the%20containment%20of%20conflict%20alone.%20It%20comes%20through%20reconciliation%2C%20through%20abjuring%20the%20notion%20of%20victor%E2%80%99s%20justice%2C%20and%20through%20compassion.%20This%20is%20important%20because%20no%20society%20is%20free%20of%20violence.%20The%20beast%20lurks%20on%20the%20sidelines%2C%20waiting%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20enter%20and%20wreck%20the%20lives%20of%20our%20people.%20Statesmen%20know%20how%20to%20contain%20the%20beast%20and%20keep%20it%20at%20the%20boundaries%20of%20society.%20Will%20politicians%20learn%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fneera-chandhoke%5C%22%3ENeera%20Chandhoke%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Delhi%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691494185000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140816%2F13500839884_2eac74d6c1_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Findia-nelson-mandela-idea-peace-reconciliation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Though%20he%20founded%20the%20armed%20wing%20of%20the%20African%20Nationalist%20Congress%2C%20Mandela%20adopted%20a%20different%20ideal%20for%20tackling%20historical%20injustices%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20release.%20He%20realised%20that%20peace%20and%20reconciliation%20were%20essential%20preconditions%20of%20democracy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Findia-nelson-mandela-idea-peace-reconciliation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gal%20on%20her%20special%20connection%20with%20Alia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691493867000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102535876%2Cimgsize-102996.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fgal-gadot-talks-about-the-reasons-for-her-special-connection-with-alia-bhatt%2Farticleshow%2F102535876.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102535876.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20popularity%20of%20Alia%20Bhatt's%20most%20recent%20movie%2C%20Rocky%20Aur%20Rani%20Kii%20Prem%20Kahaani%2C%20which%20also%20stars%20Ranveer%20Singh%20and%20is%20dir