s%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banks%20Wrote%20off%20Rs%2014.56%20Lakh%20Crore%20Since%202014-15%3A%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2F24173925%2Fcurrency_pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Banks%20have%20written%20off%20bad%20loans%20worth%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20financial%20years%20starting%202014-15%2C%20parliament%20was%20informed%20on%20Monday%2C%20August%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20PTI%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%2014%2C56%2C226%20crore%2C%20written%20off%20loans%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%20stood%20at%20Rs%207%2C40%2C968%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScheduled%20Commercial%20Banks%20have%20recovered%20an%20aggregate%20amount%20of%20Rs%202%2C04%2C668%20crore%20in%20written-off%20loans%2C%20including%20corporate%20loans%2C%20since%20April%202014%20and%20up%20to%20March%2C%202023%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Finance%20Bhagwat%20Karad%20said%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20another%20reply%20by%20the%20minister%2C%20the%20net%20of%20recovery%20in%20written-off%20loans%20during%20the%20financial%20year%20(net%20write-off)%20in%20public%20sector%20banks%20(PSBs)%20was%20Rs%201.18%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20FY18%2C%20which%20declined%20to%20Rs%200.91%20lakh%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20to%20Rs%200.84%20lakh%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20loans%20by%20private%20sector%20banks%20stood%20at%20Rs%2073%2C803%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20as%20percentage%20of%20opening%20gross%20loans%20and%20advances%20in%20private%20sector%20banks%20was%201.25%25%20and%201.57%25%20in%20FY18%20and%20FY23%2C%20respectively.%20It%20was%202%25%20and%201.12%25%20for%20PSBs%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20banks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%5C%22%3Ewrote%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20worth%20over%20Rs%202.09%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24%2025.50%20billion)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20total%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20the%20banking%20sector%20stood%20at%20Rs%2010.57%20lakh%20crore%2C%20the%20Indian%20Express%20reported%2C%20citing%20an%20RTI%20response%20from%20the%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20loan%20is%20classified%20as%20an%20NPA%20when%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20principal%20amount%20or%20the%20interest%20remains%20outstanding%20for%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20measures%20taken%20to%20bring%20down%20bad%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20asset%20growth%2C%20the%20board%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20in%20its%20meeting%20held%20on%20June%209%20had%20approved%20raising%20capital%20through%20bonds%2C%20including%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20Basel%20III%20compliant%20AT-1%20bonds%2C%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20via%20Tier-2%20bonds%2C%20and%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20infrastructure%20bonds%20during%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Karad%2C%20banks%20are%20exempted%20from%20maintaining%20cash%20reserve%20ratio%20and%20statutory%20liquidity%20ratio%20on%20long-term%20bonds%20for%20lending%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20sector.%20The%20raising%20of%20long-term%20infrastructure%20bonds%20helps%20the%20bank%20in%20better%20asset%20liability%20management%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20steps%20to%20bring%20down%20NPAs%2C%20the%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Securitisation%20and%20Reconstruction%20of%20Financial%20Assets%20and%20Enforcement%20of%20Security%20Interest%20Act%2C%202002%2C%20has%20been%20amended%20to%20make%20it%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20monetary%20limit%20for%20filing%20cases%20in%20debt%20recovery%20tribunals%20(DRTs)%20was%20increased%20from%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2020%20lakh.%20This%20enables%20the%20DRTs%20to%20focus%20on%20high-value%20cases%2C%20resulting%20in%20higher%20recovery%20for%20the%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20the%20National%20Asset%20Reconstruction%20Company%20Limited%20(NARCL)%20has%20been%20set%20up%20as%20an%20asset%20reconstruction%20company%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20resolve%20stressed%20assets%20above%20Rs%20500%20crore%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20is%20bad%20bank%2C%20which%20buys%20NPAs%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20from%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20acquired%20three%20borrower%20entities%2C%20including%20Jaypee%20Infratech%2C%20with%20an%20aggregate%20debt%20exposure%20of%20Rs%2021%2C349%20crore%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%20FY23%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Findustry%2Fnarcl-acquires-rs-21349-cr-toxic-assets-far-cry-from-target%2F3185153%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20targets%20set%20for%20transfer%20of%20toxic%20assets%20to%20the%20NARCL.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20the%20NARCL%20got%20a%20licence%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20start%20operations%2C%20and%20as%20per%20the%20initial%20target%2C%20it%20was%20to%20acquire%20a%20batc