2%3A%22The%20Dangerous%20Salesman%20of%20Science%C2%A0%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140248%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.02.24-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%201987%20Nobel%20lecture%2C%20Joseph%20Brodsky%20said%2C%20anthropologically%20speaking%2C%20a%20human%20being%20is%20primarily%20a%20creature%20of%20aesthetics%2C%20and%20only%20after%2C%20an%20ethical%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20assertion%20sounds%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20J.%20Robert%20Oppenheimer.%20The%20scientific%20leaps%20in%20the%20field%20of%20quantum%20physics%20fascinated%20Oppenheimer.%20He%20was%20driven%20to%20follow%20the%20path%20of%20Niels%20Bohr%20and%20Werner%20Heisenberg.%20Returning%20from%20Cambridge%20to%20expand%20his%20research%20in%20Berkeley%2C%20he%20fell%20into%20the%20arms%20of%20the%20American%20state%20and%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%20to%20develop%20an%20atomic%20bomb.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20comic%20irony%20that%20Lewis%20Strauss%2C%20who%20secretly%20plotted%20against%20Oppenheimer%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20work%20as%20a%20shoe%20salesman%20during%20the%20recession%2C%20while%20Oppenheimer%20achieved%20the%20distinction%20of%20Edward%20Teller%20calling%20him%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20great%20salesman%20of%20science.%E2%80%9D%20This%20explains%20the%20moral%20turn%20in%20the%20life%20of%20Oppenheimer.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DuYPbbksJxIg%26ab_channel%3DUniversalPictures%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Nolan%20likened%20his%20character%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20titan%20Prometheus%2C%20though%20midway%20he%20seemed%20to%20metamorphose%20into%20Frankenstein.%20The%20hamartia%20of%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20term%20for%20the%20Greek%20tragic%20hero%E2%80%99s%20fatal%20flaw%2C%20turned%20into%20a%20modern%20horror%20story.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20poet%20Joseph%20Brodsky%E2%80%99s%20distinction%20becomes%20relevant%20at%20this%20point%3A%20Oppenheimer%20abandoned%20the%20moral%20for%20the%20aesthetic.%20My%20scholar%20friend%20(who%20wishes%20to%20remain%20unnamed)%20shared%20the%20opinion%20that%20Oppenheimer%2C%20initially%20lost%20in%20the%20beauty%20of%20pure%20theory%2C%20transforms%20that%20aesthetic%20obsession%20into%20a%20monstrous%20one.%20She%20added%20the%20sharp%20insight%3A%20%E2%80%9COppenheimer%20tells%20himself%20a%20lie.%20That%20the%20bomb%20has%20a%20moral%20end.%E2%80%9D%20The%20act%20of%20lying%20to%20oneself%20produced%20a%20psychic%20wound%20within%20Oppenheimer.%20He%20lost%20sight%20of%20the%20moral%20aspect%20within%20his%20aesthetic%20pursuit.%20The%20lie%20made%20the%20transformation%20possible.%20The%20sublime%20beauty%20of%20studying%20quantum%20physics%20was%20ruined%20the%20moment%20Oppenheimer%20decided%20to%20use%20his%20expertise%20for%20a%20detrimental%20cause.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140304%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.01.03-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140304%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.01.03-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140304%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.01.03-PM-300x135.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140304%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.01.03-PM-1024x461.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667152%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20the%20film%20%E2%80%98Oppenheimer%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sale%20of%20his%20scientific%20skills%20to%20the%20American%20state%20for%20making%20the%20bomb%20had%20a%20clear%20political%20objective%20for%20Oppenheimer%3A%20to%20finish%20off%20Hitler.%20This%20logic%20led%20him%20to%20overcome%20the%20moral%20dilemma%20behind%20his%20job.%20Any%20force%20that%20can%20destroy%20evil%20is%20legitimate.%20The%20destructive%20power%20of%20science%20was%20a%20seductive%20option%20to%20nullify%20the%20power%20of%20fascism.%20The%20Jewish%20Oppenheimer%20did%20not%20have%20his%20revenge%20over%20the%20Nazis%20(who%20were%20already%20defeated%20when%20the%20bomb%20was%20ready).%20The%20American%20state%20used%20it%20against%20a%20weakened%20Japan%20to%20declare%20its%20omnipotence.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYoung%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20T.S.%20Eliot%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98The%20Wasteland%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGita%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20a%20deep%20connection%3A%20Eliot%E2%80%99s%20poem%20ends%20by%20evoking%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUpanishad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CShantih%20shantih%20shantih%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20peace%20of%20the%20grave%20that%20fell%20upon%20a%20world%20torn%20apart%20by%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20I%20and%20the%20flu%20epidemic.%20Oppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20the%20line%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGita%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20become%20Death%2C%20destroyer%20of%20worlds%E2%80%9D%20was%20what%20Krishna%20said%20about%20his%20divinity%20being%20time%20itself%20that%20destroys%20the%20world%20at%20will.%20It%20was%20meant%20to%20exhort%20a%20weak-kneed%20Arjuna%20(who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20kill%20his%20cousins%2C%20seniors%20and%20kinsmen)%2C%20reminding%20him%20of%20his%20duty%20as%20a%20warrior%20to%20prepare%20him%20for%20battle.%20The%20figure%20of%20divine%20incarnation%20and%20warrior-prince%20got%20fused%20into%20the%20scientist%20who%20invented%20a%20weapon%20that%20could%20kill%20millions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOppenheimer%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20the%20evocative%20moments%20in%20the%20two%20texts%20shows%20a%20certain%20death%20wish%20he%20carried%20within%20himself.%20When%20you%20are%20hell-bent%20to%20destroy%20the%20enemy%2C%20you%20are%20also%20out%20to%20kill%20a%20part%20of%20yourself%20through%20the%20act%20of%20retributive%20justice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOppenheimer%20was%20not%20able%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20ethical%20difference%20between%20annihilating%20a%20system%20of%20power%20and%20annihilating%20people.%20This%20failure%2C%20however%2C%20is%20an%20intimate%20part%20of%20the%20modern%20West%E2%80%99s%20history.%20It%20produced%20ideas%20of%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20fascism%2C%20communism%20and%20imperial%20democracies%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20other%20within%20and%20outside%20one%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20fold%20was%20demonised%20as%20the%20absolute%20enemy%20and%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20exterminated.%20Making%20the%20bomb%20to%20be%20used%20for%20war%2C%20Oppenheimer%20not%20just%20used%20science%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20destruction%2C%20but%20created%20an%20ideology%20of%20science%20as%20divine%20power%20that%20could%20kill%20uncountable%20numbers%20of%20people%20as%20much%20as%20it%20could%20heal%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20been%20acknowledged%20that%20Nolan%20did%20not%20glorify%20war%20by%20not%20showing%20the%20bomb%20being%20dropped%20on%20the%20two%20Japanese%20cities.%20Still%2C%20as%20my%20scholar%20friend%20pointed%20out%2C%20Nolan%20could%20not%20prevent%20himself%20from%20indulging%20in%20Hollywood%E2%80%99s%20fetish%20for%20spectacle.%20There%20was%20a%20clear%20lack%20of%20self-restraint.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20slow-motion%20explosion%20of%20the%20bomb%20that%20filled%20the%20screen%20numbed%20the%20audience%2C%20and%20engulfed%20it%20into%20the%20terror%20of%20its%20silence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EContrast%20it%20with%20Abbas%20Kiarostami%2C%20who%20did%20not%20display%20the%20earthquakes%20that%20rocked%20Iran%20in%20Koker%20Trilogy%20in%20order%20to%20portray%20its%20psycho-social%20repercussion%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20residents%20who%20suffered%20its%20impact.%20Kiarostami%E2%80%99s%20art%20of%20filmmaking%20is%20deeply%20informed%20by%20his%20ethical%20hesitation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08134623%2FKiarostami_And-Life-Goes-On_006_1200.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08134623%2FKiarostami_And-Life-Goes-On_006_1200.jpg%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08134623%2FKiarostami_And-Life-Goes-On_006_1200-300x194.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667149%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22420%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20Abbas%20Kiarostami%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98And%20Life%20Goes%20on%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENolan%20had%20more%20reasons%20to%20hold%20back%20from%20depicting%20the%20technological%20grandeur%20of%20an%20instrument%20of%20death.%20The%20temptation%20to%20recreate%20the%20spectacle%20is%20not%20simply%20an%20aesthetic%20flaw.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20euphoria%20of%20the%20scientific%20feat%20was%20viscerally%20exhibited%20by%20bodies%20of%20people%20stomping%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20hall%20celebrating%20Oppenheimer.%20It%20announced%20the%20coming%20of%20a%20new%20crowd%20in%20world%20history%20that%20took%20nationalist%20pride%20in%20mass%20destruction%20of%20other%20people.%20Oppenheimer%20looked%20conflicted%2C%20remorseful%20and%20eaten%20by%20guilt.%20But%20there%20were%20no%20indications%20to%20suggest%20he%20completely%20regretted%20his%20success.%20Truman%2C%20embodying%20the%20masculine%20pragmatism%20of%20the%20American%20state%2C%20lampooned%20Oppenheimer%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccrybaby%E2%80%9D.%20No%20one%20cared%20about%20the%20real%20babies%20in%20Hiroshima%20and%20Nagasaki.%20Such%20is%20the%20moral%20indifference%20of%20war.%20It%20causes%20deafness%20of%20the%20soul.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EManash%20Firaq%20Bhattacharjee%20is%20an%20author.%20His%20latest%20book%20is%20%3C%2Fem%3ENehru%20and%20the%20Spirit%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691483870000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08140248%2FScreenshot-2023-08-08-at-2.02.24-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Foppenheimer-nolan-science-salesman%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Oppenheimer%20tells%20himself%20a%20lie%2C%20says%20my%20scholar%20friend.%20'That%20the%20bomb%20has%20a%20moral%20end.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Foppenheimer-nolan-science-salesman%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Italy%20introduces%20surprise%20windfall%20tax%20on%20banks'%20interest%20rate%20profits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691483760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-intesa-sanpaolo-italy_6243949.jpg%3F20230808095052%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fitaly-introduces-surprise-windfall-tax-on-banks-interest-rate-profits-12935871%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Italian%20government%20has%20introduced%20a%20surprise%2040%25%20windfall%20tax%20on%20the%20pr