s%20January%202020%20election%20conspiracy%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20arguing%20the%20order%20would%20violate%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20First%20Amendment%20right%20to%20free%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20have%20said%20that%C2%A0confidential%20documents%20and%20evidence%20they%20would%20share%20with%20the%20former%20president%20during%20the%20trial%20must%20be%20protected.%20Prosecutors%20expressed%20concern%20that%20Trump%20could%20use%20the%C2%A0information%20in%20the%20documents%20to%20intimidate%20individuals%20related%20to%20the%20trial%2C%20including%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20protective%20order%20would%20restrict%20the%20information%20Trump%20and%20his%20legal%20team%20are%20allowed%20to%20share%20with%20unauthorized%20personnel.%20It%20aims%20to%20protect%20the%20classified%20documents%20and%20information%20prosecutors%20must%20share%20with%20the%20defendant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20it%20could%20prohibit%20Trump%20from%20making%20such%20material%20public%20during%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20legal%20team%20say%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20legal%20team%20submitted%20a%2029-page%20filing%20to%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20in%20Washington%20as%20a%20response.%20They%20acknowledged%20the%20importance%20of%20shielding%20some%20of%20the%20documents%20from%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20need%20to%20protect%20that%20information%20does%20not%20require%20a%20blanket%20gag%20order%20over%20all%20documents%20produced%20by%20the%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20wrote%20in%20the%20court%20papers%20filed%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20suggested%20a%20more%20limited%20order%20that%20does%20not%20include%20all%20documents%20shared%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20filing%2C%20nevertheless%2C%20did%20not%20directly%20address%20the%20assertion%20of%20witness%20intimidation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20trial%20about%20First%20Amendment%20rights%2C%20the%20government%20seeks%20to%20restrict%20First%20Amendment%20rights%2C%E2%80%9D%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20attorneys%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20right%20of%20free%20speech%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20US%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20prompted%20the%20prosecutors%E2%80%99%20request%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20request%20came%20after%20Trump%20posted%20what%20was%20perceived%20to%20be%20a%20threatening%20statement%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%2C%20Truth%20Social.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20facing%20a%20judge%20to%20plead%20not%20guilty%20over%20his%20indictment%20on%20charges%20that%20he%20engaged%20in%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20of%20the%202020%20election%2C%20Trump%20posted%20in%20all%20caps%3A%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20go%20after%20me%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20coming%20after%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20suspected%20the%20post%20was%20a%20threat%20to%20anyone%20involved%20in%20the%20trial%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%E2%80%99s%20indictment%20on%20charges%20of%20conspiring%20to%20overturn%20his%202020%20election%20loss%C2%A0is%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftrump-faces-new-charges-in-florida-classified-documents-case%2Fa-66372588%5C%22%3Ethird%20in%20four%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20Trump.%C2%A0He%20is%20nonetheless%20currently%20considered%20the%20frontrunner%20in%20a%20campaign%20to%20become%20the%202024%20Republican%20nominee%20for%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftrump-argues-protective-order-would-violate-his-free-speech%2Fa-66465796%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691480717000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3