f%20Telangana.%20He%20symbolised%20the%20energy%20of%20the%20time%20of%20revolutionary%20politics%20and%20was%20its%20greatest%20makings.%20His%20songs%20were%20not%20just%20an%20art%20but%20a%20phenomenon.%20His%20songs%20were%20listened%20to%20and%20appreciated%20cutting%20across%20classes.%20He%20had%20a%20unique%20reach%20into%20the%20drawing%20rooms%20and%20playing%20recorders%20of%20the%20rich%20and%20dominant%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FIcbJDYmRmUY%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20this%20reflect%20the%20aesthetic%20symbolism%20of%20the%20song%20or%20the%20power%20of%20revolutionary%20imagination%3F%20There%20is%20a%20famous%20incident%20when%20Gaddar%20had%20to%20visit%20a%20police%20station%20in%20relation%20to%20a%20case%20filed%20against%20him%20where%20the%20constables%2C%20much%20to%20the%20annoyance%20of%20the%20sub-inspector%20requested%20him%20to%20sing%20a%20song%20and%20seek%20out%20photops.%20He%20transcended%20social%20divides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20course%20of%20a%20personal%20conversation%2C%20a%20long%20time%20back%2C%20he%20narrated%20the%20incident%20when%20he%20was%20%E2%80%98underground%E2%80%99%20living%20an%20anonymous%20life%20he%20use%20to%20sing%20songs%20as%20part%20of%20the%20band%20of%20followers%20of%20Lord%20Ayappa.%20He%20narrated%20the%20power%20of%20the%20chant%20and%20the%20power%20of%20repeating%20a%20chant%2C%20and%20how%20drew%20on%20even%20religious%20tunes%2C%20symbols%2C%20and%20songs%20for%20revolutionary%20messages.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20Gaddar%E2%80%99s%20lyrics%2C%20religious%20symbols%20became%20art%20and%20cultural%20symbols.%20The%20symbolism%20of%20the%20rising%20sun%20would%20alternate%20between%20religious%20sensibilities%20and%20revolutionary%20emotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20once%20famously%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20emotionalise%20the%20revolution%20but%20revolutionise%20emotions.%E2%80%9D%20His%20symbolism%20moved%20seamlessly%20from%20the%20everyday%20to%20the%20heroic.%20He%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20saw%20the%20heroic%20in%20the%20everyday.%20From%20ants%2C%20to%20leaves%2C%20to%20flowers%2C%20to%20hills%2C%20to%20oceans%20to%20forests%2C%20to%20people%20and%20their%20suffering.%20Nothing%20escaped%20the%20symbolic%20potential%20of%20his%20lyrics.%20It%20is%20this%20emotional%20appeal%2C%20symbolism%2C%20and%20aesthetic%20power%20that%20was%20the%20substance%20of%20his%20public%20performances%20before%20lakhs%20of%20people%20that%20on%20some%20occasions%20went%20through%20all%20night%20and%20ended%20in%20the%20wee%20hours%20of%20dawn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20the%20memorable%20opportunity%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20audience%20of%20many%20such%20captivating%20performances%2C%20where%20his%20performances%20seamlessly%20alternated%20humour%20and%20the%20finality%20of%20death%20in%20revolutionary%20politics.%20These%20were%20the%20ethics%20and%20emotions%20that%20were%20somewhat%20uncommon%20and%20continue%20to%20inform%20public%20life%20in%20Telangana%20to%20a%20fair%20degree.%20People%20in%20all%20walks%20of%20life%20were%20touched%20in%20known%20and%20unknown%20ways%20by%20the%20spirit%20of%20Gaddar%E2%80%99s%20performance%20and%20the%20message%20it%20brought%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201997%20he%20was%20shot%20at%2C%20allegedly%20by%20the%20police%20in%20plain%20clothes.%20It%20was%20a%20punishment%20for%20garnering%20popular%20support%20for%20revolutionary%20forces%2C%20but%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20Gaddar%20was%20mobilising%20popular%20sentiment%20for%20those%20falling%20dead%20in%20alleged%20fake%20encounters%20by%20the%20police%20and%20Greyhounds.%20He%20miraculously%20survived%20the%20attempt%20at%20assassination%20and%20carried%20five%20bullets%20in%20his%20body%2C%20as%20he%20could%20not%20be%20operated%20upon%20due%20to%20advancing%20age%20and%20other%20health-related%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGaddar%20and%20Telangana%20statehood%20movement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20destiny%20would%20have%20it%2C%20the%20face%20of%20revolution%20in%20Telangana%20got%20distanced%20from%20revolutionary%20politics%20due%20to%20issues%20of%20propriety%20and%20other%20differences.%20This%20was%20the%20last%20phase%20of%20Gaddar%E2%80%99s%20public%20life%20in%20Telangana.%20Many%20believe%20the%20power%20and%20popular%20appeal%20of%20his%20songs%20and%20performances%20drastically%20reduced%20after%20his%20distancing%20from%20revolutionary%20politics.%20But%20revolutionary%20politics%20too%20lost%20a%20voice%20that%20had%20the%20greatest%20power%20of%20communicating%20cutting%20across%20social%20divides.%20The%20power%20of%20the%20symbolism%20of%20his%20rebellious%20songs%20went%20pale%20without%20the%20revolutionary%20spirit%20and%20politics%20behind%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20this%20was%20tragic%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Telangana%20continued%20to%20remember%20and%20accept%20Gaddar%20only%20as%20a%20revolutionary%20balladeer.%20Wherever%20he%20travelled%20people%20requested%20him%20to%20sing%20his%20revolutionary%20songs%20that%20paid%20tribute%20to%20those%20slain%20in%20the%20course%20of%20revolutionary%20politics.%20It%20reminds%20one%20of%20what%20Shahid%20Amin%20wrote%20of%20%3Cem%3EGandhi%20as%20Mahatma%3C%2Fem%3E%20who%20carried%20multiple%20images%20of%20a%20saint%2C%20a%20healer%2C%20and%20a%20God%20in%20peasant%20consciousness.%20Peasants%20and%20the%20common%20masses%20of%20Telangana%20refused%20to%20see%20Gaddar%20as%20anything%20else%20than%20a%20rebellious%20figure.%20The%20image%20of%20him%20in%20a%20red-coloured%20rug%20was%20stuck%20in%20popular%20memory.%20The%20people%20of%20Telangana%20continued%20to%20live%20with%20that%20singular%20image.%20As%20Milan%20Kundera%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20struggle%20of%20man%20against%20power%20is%20the%20struggle%20of%20memory%20against%20forgetting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaddar%20attempted%20to%20move%20to%20mainstream%20electoral%20politics%20and%20party%20politics%2C%20but%20his%20revolutionary%20image%20and%20radical%20symbolism%20would%20hardly%20fit%20with%20power%20politics.%20It%20seems%20to%20break%20the%20alliteration%20aesthetics%20demanded%2C%20though%20he%20attempted%20to%20equate%20the%20power%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98ballot%E2%80%99%20over%20the%20bullet.%20However%2C%20it%20could%20not%20garner%20the%20same%20feverish%20pitch%20that%20he%20could%20reach%20in%20his%20heydays.%20He%20later%20struck%20a%20chord%20during%20the%20movement%20for%20separate%20Telangana.%20He%20penned%20a%20song%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Epodusthunna%20poddumeeda%20nadusthinna%20kalaama%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20roughly%20symbolised%20Telangana%20as%20a%20rising%20sun%20that%20time%20awaits.%20It%20became%20the%20anthem%20song%20of%20the%20mass%20movement%20for%20separate%20Telangana.%20No%20public%20meeting%20could%20end%20with%20either%20Gaddar%20himself%20or%20his%20countless%20admirers%20singing%20the%20song%20to%20rousing%20applause.%20Gaddar%20once%20again%20captured%20the%20spirit%20behind%20the%20times%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FBn5XMi8HfrE%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20called%20Gaddar%20leaves%20behind%20a%20legacy%20and%20a%20range%20of%20questions%20that%20will%20further%20illuminate%20the%20collective%20spirit%20of%20Telangana.%20He%20symbolised%20a%20seamless%20unison%20of%20collective%20making%20and%20a%20freak%20genius%20who%20could%20captivate%20the%20pulse%20through%20his%20words%20and%20lyrics.%20He%20had%20a%20childlike%20curiosity%2C%20humour%20and%20anarchy%20that%20could%20not%20be%20contained%20by%20reason%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20Telugu%20movie%2C%20%3Cem%3EVirata%20Parvam%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecaptured%20the%20tension%20between%20reason%20and%20emotion%2C%20between%20strategy%20and%20love%2C%20and%20between%20un-reflexive%20attachment%20and%20informed%20detachment.%20Gaddar%20too%20is%20part%20and%20product%20of%20that%20tension.%20He%20transcended%20the%20political%20through%20aesthetics%20and%20politicised%20the%20symbolic.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20revolution%20without%20a%20%E2%80%98Gaddar%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20there%20can%2C%20perhaps%20be%20no%20%E2%80%98Gaddar%E2%80%99%20without%20a%20collective%20spirit.%20It%20is%20this%20undying%20collective%20spirit%20that%20Gaddar%20will%20continue%20to%20symbolise%20in%20humanity%E2%80%99s%20search%20to%20transcend%20the%20banal%20and%20here-and-now%20dictates%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmigrant-workers-middle-class-lockdown%5C%22%3EAjay%20Gudavarthy%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20JNU.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691480705000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08125021%2FUntitled-design-2023-08-08T124943.925.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgaddar-who-symbolised-revolutionary-politics-leaves-behind-questions-on-social-transformation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He%20transcended%20the%20political%20through%20aesthetics%20and%20politicised%20the%20symbolic.%20For%20a%20generation%2C%20he%20symbolised%20the%20spirit%20and%20politics%20of%20revolutionary%20change%2C%20primarily%20in%20Telangana%2C%20but%20his%20songs%20travelled%20well%20beyond.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%